Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.41,0:01:01.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\fs90}Thank you. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.94,0:01:08.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常感谢\N{\fs90}Thank you very much. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.94,0:01:20.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢大家 欢迎来到伟大的旅程\N{\fs90}Danke. Danke und willkommen in der Große Tour
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.32,0:01:21.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,本期节目来自德国\N{\fs90}which this week comes from Germany!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.94,0:01:26.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 我们来了\N{\fs90}Ja. We're here. We're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.05,0:01:32.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,准确地说 这里是斯图加特\N{\fs90}Specifically... Specifically, we are in the city of Stuttgart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.30,0:01:34.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们差点来不了\N{\fs90}Except we nearly weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.58,0:01:37.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你们当地的一位绿党政治家\N{\fs90}Because one of your local Green politicians
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.53,0:01:39.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,试图禁止入境\N{\fs90}tried to ban us from coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.01,0:01:42.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不想在节目上让他难堪\N{\fs90}I don't want to embarrass the poor man on television.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.61,0:01:44.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们隐匿了他的身份\N{\fs90}So I've hidden his identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.67,0:01:50.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\fs90}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.24,0:01:51.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是啊  -这很好\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.07,0:01:55.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常恰当\N{\fs90}That's appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.41,0:01:58.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,我肯定不会告诉你们他的名字\N{\fs90}I certainly don't want to tell you his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.08,0:02:01.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是Andreas Kasdorf(德国绿党成员)\N{\fs90}Which is... Andreas Kasdorf.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.22,0:02:07.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,不太受欢迎啊 但你们投票选了他\N{\fs90}Not a popular man. But you elected him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.27,0:02:11.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,总之 他说不欢迎我们来这儿\N{\fs90}Anyway, he says that we'd be unwelcome here
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.43,0:02:14.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这是个自行车友好城市\N{\fs90}because this is a very bicycle-friendly place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.80,0:02:19.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,才怪 这是奔驰和保时捷的家乡\N{\fs90}It... It isn't. It's the home of Mercedes and Porsche.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.43,0:02:22.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,-德国还是  -正是\N{\fs90}- And Germany... - Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.64,0:02:25.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,德国\N{\fs90}Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.71,0:02:29.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,德国是汽车工业的摇篮\N{\fs90}Germany is the cradle of the automobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.87,0:02:31.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,汽车就是在这发明的\N{\fs90}The car was actually invented here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.03,0:02:34.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是地球上唯一一个地方\N{\fs90}It's the last place on Earth you can drive a car
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.85,0:02:37.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,你能在高速上开到极速\N{\fs90}as fast as it will go on the motorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.02,0:02:40.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,-实话  -大实话\N{\fs90}- It's true. - All true.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.49,0:02:43.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是铁打的事实\N{\fs90}This is a true fact. This is a true fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.01,0:02:46.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,德国人是唯一\N{\fs90}The Germans are the only people on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.41,0:02:49.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,真正知道如何造车的人\N{\fs90}who really know how to make a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.33,0:02:51.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是\N{\fs90}This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.13,0:02:54.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是不争的事实  -对\N{\fs90}- It's a true fact. - It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.14,0:02:55.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,给你们讲个故事\N{\fs90}I'll tell you a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.70,0:02:57.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,某晚 一个奔驰工程师\N{\fs90}There was a Mercedes engineer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.14,0:02:59.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,和一个捷豹工程师吃饭\N{\fs90}and a Jaguar engineer having dinner one night.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.87,0:03:02.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,奔驰工程师说 俺们有\N{\fs90}The Mercedes engineer said, "Ve haf..."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.28,0:03:03.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,原谅我的口音(模仿德国口音)\N{\fs90}Forgive the accent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.68,0:03:07.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,奔驰车间里有个质量测试\N{\fs90}"Ve haf a quality test at ze Mercedes factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.32,0:03:10.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,每晚 我们随机挑一辆生产线上的车\N{\fs90}Every night, ve take a car off ze line at random.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.52,0:03:14.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,在里面放只猫 关上门\N{\fs90}Ve put a cat in it, close ze doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.18,0:03:16.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果早上我们回来的时候\N{\fs90}If... When ve come back in ze morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.26,0:03:18.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,猫闷死了\N{\fs90}ve know the door seals are vorking correctly
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.90,0:03:21.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,就能确定车门密封性很好\N{\fs90}if ze cat has suffocated."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.47,0:03:25.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs90}Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.97,0:03:27.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,捷豹工程师说\N{\fs90}The Jaguar engineer said,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.87,0:03:30.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们车间也有类似的测试\N{\fs90}"We've got something very similar at our factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.61,0:03:32.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,先从流水线上挑一辆车\N{\fs90}We take a car off the line at random.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.65,0:03:35.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,放只猫进去 关上车门\N{\fs90}We put a cat in it. We close the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.12,0:03:37.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果隔天早上看到猫还在\N{\fs90}And we know the car's been built properly
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:40.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们就知道车质量合格了\N{\fs90}if, when we come back in the morning, the cat hasn't escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.01,0:03:42.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,真事\N{\fs90}That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.98,0:03:45.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,-真事  -对的\N{\fs90}- True story. - Yeah. True story.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:47.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,奇怪的是\N{\fs90}The strange thing is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.52,0:03:49.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不仅车造得好\N{\fs90}it isn't just cars that are built well here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.92,0:03:52.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,-一切都很好  -除了红酒\N{\fs90}- It's absolutely everything. - Except wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.89,0:03:54.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 不好意思 除了红酒\N{\fs90}Yes, except wine. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.93,0:03:56.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是吧\N{\fs90}Well, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.65,0:03:59.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,-拜托  -你们喝那玩意儿吗\N{\fs90}- Now come on! - You drink that stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.44,0:04:02.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,拿来洗头我都嫌弃\N{\fs90}I wouldn't wash my hair in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:03.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,你确定吗\N{\fs90}Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:05.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的是所有工艺都精湛\N{\fs90}It is literally everything, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.34,0:04:06.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,德国毛绒玩具\N{\fs90}German soft toys,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.63,0:04:08.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,最好的毛绒玩具\N{\fs90}better than anybody else's soft toys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.41,0:04:10.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,照相机 厨房用具\N{\fs90}Cameras, kitchen appliances.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.85,0:04:13.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,英国女皇 她也是德国产的\N{\fs90}The Queen of England, she's German.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.48,0:04:15.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的 这就是为什么\N{\fs90}She is. That's why she's still working
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.01,0:04:18.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,她都157岁了还没罢工\N{\fs90}even though she's a hundred and forty seventeen years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.72,0:04:21.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,这儿的字典没有"还行"二字\N{\fs90}There is no word here for "that'll do".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.42,0:04:24.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,在德国没有模棱两可的说法\N{\fs90}There is no ambiguity at all in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.89,0:04:26.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,从电影名中就看出来\N{\fs90}You certainly see this with films.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.76,0:04:29.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们给美国电影起的名字\N{\fs90}The names you have for American films.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.78,0:04:32.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我这有一些 记得Airplane这部电影吗\N{\fs90}I've got some here. Remember Airplane?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.27,0:04:34.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,Airplane 记得(1980年美国电影 中文译名"空前绝后满天飞")\N{\fs90}Airplane, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.07,0:04:35.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,在德国 它叫做\N{\fs90}In Germany, it was called
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.78,0:04:39.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,失控飞机中的不思议之旅\N{\fs90}The Unbelievable Journey In The Crazy Airplane.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.47,0:04:42.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个标题很直观\N{\fs90}That is a comprehensive title.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.10,0:04:43.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,一看就知道内容是什么\N{\fs90}You know where you are with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.08,0:04:44.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,大白鲨在这叫什么\N{\fs90}What was Jaws?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.91,0:04:47.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么 白色的\N{\fs90}The what? The Weiße...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.95,0:04:49.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,白色的鲨鱼\N{\fs90}The White Shark.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.72,0:04:51.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,应该叫巨型鲨鱼\N{\fs90}It should have been The Massive Shark...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.72,0:04:54.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,最终炸了\N{\fs90}...That Explodes Eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.32,0:04:56.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,一看也知道在讲什么\N{\fs90}You know where you're going with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.46,0:04:58.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,本能的译名呢\N{\fs90}What was... What was Basic Instinct?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.38,0:05:00.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,难道不是\N{\fs90}Just not
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.05,0:05:03.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,莎朗·斯通私处的匆匆一瞥吗\N{\fs90}A Brief Glimpse Of Sharon Stone's Vagina?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.67,0:05:06.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们能继续节目吗  -好主意\N{\fs90}- Shall we get on with the show? - Yes, good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.27,0:05:08.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,在今晚的汽车节目中\N{\fs90}Because in tonight's car programme...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.90,0:05:12.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,理查德遛了条狗\N{\fs90}Richard walks a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.31,0:05:15.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯在健身房晃悠\N{\fs90}James hangs around a gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.28,0:05:19.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说了好枪法\N{\fs90}And I say "Good shot."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.07,0:05:21.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,好枪法\N{\fs90}Good shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.52,0:05:23.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,但在那之前 我想谈一下\N{\fs90}But before all that, I'd like to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.32,0:05:25.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,初代本田NSX\N{\fs90}about the original Honda NSX.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.75,0:05:27.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里有张照片\N{\fs90}We have a picture of it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.46,0:05:29.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,1990年推出这车时\N{\fs90}When that car was launched in 1990,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.94,0:05:31.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,简直令人惊叹\N{\fs90}it was considered remarkable
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.98,0:05:34.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它和法拉利一样快 一样刺激\N{\fs90}because it was fast and exciting like a Ferrari,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.72,0:05:36.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,但又和当时的法拉利不同\N{\fs90}but unlike a Ferrari of the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.66,0:05:39.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,它质量极其可靠\N{\fs90}it was also incredibly reliable
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.27,0:05:41.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,操控性非常之好\N{\fs90}and very, very easy to drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.47,0:05:43.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,12年前本田砍掉了这款车型\N{\fs90}Honda killed that car off 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.85,0:05:46.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,但最终 他们推出了替代品\N{\fs90}But finally, they've come up with a replacement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.63,0:05:50.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我到了我们的赛道上一探究竟\N{\fs90}So I've been down to our track to see what it's like.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.31,0:05:54.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是它了\N{\fs90}This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.58,0:05:59.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,价值13.8万\N{\fs90}It costs £138,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.07,0:06:03.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,和保时捷911 turbo S差不多\N{\fs90}Around the same as a Porsche 911 Turbo S.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.39,0:06:05.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,线条极富未来感\N{\fs90}And it has the futuristic lines
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.74,0:06:08.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,正是你在限量版本田上想看到的\N{\fs90}you would expect of a rare-breed Honda.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.76,0:06:14.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,动力来源于3.5升双涡轮增压V6\N{\fs90}Power comes from a 3.5 litre twin-turbo V6.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.64,0:06:18.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,并备有一系列电动机\N{\fs90}Backed up by a squadron of electric motors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.74,0:06:24.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们一起提供了573匹马力\N{\fs90}Together, they give the NSX 573 horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.15,0:06:27.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以你会猜想这车的性能\N{\fs90}So you would assume the performance
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.67,0:06:30.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,应该不愧于此\N{\fs90}is something to shout about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.92,0:06:32.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你向本田询问\N{\fs90}Now, if you ask Honda
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.70,0:06:34.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车的技术参数\N{\fs90}for the technical information on this car,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.56,0:06:37.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们会发给你一封巨型邮件\N{\fs90}they will email you a file so enormous
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.39,0:06:39.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,大到互联网都无法承载\N{\fs90}that it actually breaks the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.36,0:06:42.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而 内容却从未提及百公里加速时间\N{\fs90}And yet, nowhere in it does it mention the 0-60 time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.96,0:06:45.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们就是拒绝透露\N{\fs90}They simply refuse to tell us what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.53,0:06:49.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,我知道现实中 百公里加速时间无关紧要\N{\fs90}I know 0-60 times are irrelevant in the real world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.21,0:06:51.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且十分幼稚 但这是辆超级跑车\N{\fs90}and they're rather childish, but look, this is a supercar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.67,0:06:54.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,它赢在极速上 这才是关键\N{\fs90}It's top trumps, isn't it? It's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:57.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我要用这个帮你们测出来\N{\fs90}So I'm gonna find out what it is for you using this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.38,0:06:59.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是个数据记录仪\N{\fs90}It is a data-o-logger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.28,0:07:05.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,进入赛道模式\N{\fs90}Right. Put it in Track mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.79,0:07:07.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,走着 弹射起步\N{\fs90}Here we go. Launch control.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.92,0:07:10.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,左脚刹车 右脚油门到底\N{\fs90}Foot on the brake. Mash the pedal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.64,0:07:25.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不确定这像GTR那样\N{\fs90}I'm not sure that was quite as neck-snapping
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.85,0:07:26.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,快得脖子都要扯断\N{\fs90}as a Nissan GTR,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.98,0:07:28.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,但也差不多了\N{\fs90}but it wasn't far off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.74,0:07:30.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,来看看结果如何\N{\fs90}Let's see what I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.98,0:07:36.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,百公里加速3.2秒\N{\fs90}3.2 seconds 0-60.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.34,0:07:42.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以这不如迈凯伦570S那么快\N{\fs90}Which means it isn't quite as fast as a McLaren 570S,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.76,0:07:45.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,也不如911 turbo S\N{\fs90}or a 911 Turbo S,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.46,0:07:48.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者法拉利488 GTB\N{\fs90}or a Ferrari 488 GTB.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.23,0:07:49.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,怪不得他们不肯说\N{\fs90}That's why they're not mentioning it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.10,0:07:54.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,本田倒是很乐意提及它的极速\N{\fs90}Honda is happy to quote the top speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.12,0:07:58.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,高达每小时307公里\N{\fs90}Which is 191 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.54,0:08:00.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,但依然比它的竞争对手慢\N{\fs90}But that too is slower than its rivals
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.81,0:08:03.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,如法拉利 保时捷 迈凯伦\N{\fs90}from Ferrari, Porsche, and McLaren.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.78,0:08:10.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以新款NSX\N{\fs90}So has the new NSX got anything
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.50,0:08:11.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,在性能上有哪点\N{\fs90}in the performance department
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.90,0:08:14.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,比同级跑车更好呢\N{\fs90}that makes it rise above its supercar peers?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.22,0:08:19.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,还真有\N{\fs90}Well, yes, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.32,0:08:22.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,首先 它的电子刹车\N{\fs90}Firstly, there are the brakes, which are fly-by-wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.10,0:08:24.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,刹车和踏板间没有物理连接\N{\fs90}There is no physical connection to the pedal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.12,0:08:26.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它们要把刹车能量回收\N{\fs90}That's because they have to harvest energy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.72,0:08:28.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,返还到电池系统\N{\fs90}to recharge the battery system.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.47,0:08:30.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,这比保时捷918的版本\N{\fs90}It's a much cleverer version of that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.50,0:08:32.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,要先进得多\N{\fs90}than you get on the Porsche 918,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.27,0:08:34.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,918还要贵5倍\N{\fs90}a car that costs five times as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.51,0:08:36.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后 混动系统\N{\fs90}Then there's the hybrid system.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.43,0:08:38.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,不止是一个电机\N{\fs90}It uses not one electric motor,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.30,0:08:40.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,它用了三个\N{\fs90}as you might expect, but three.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.10,0:08:43.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,使用方式也是别出心裁\N{\fs90}And the way it uses them is well good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.82,0:08:49.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,后面的电机\N{\fs90}The one at the back
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.27,0:08:51.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,是汽油机的僚机\N{\fs90}is the wingman for the petrol engine,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.30,0:08:54.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,涡轮迟滞时 能填补动力缺失\N{\fs90}filling the power gaps when the turbos lag.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.56,0:08:59.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,这让NSX在任何速度下都能如出膛般加速\N{\fs90}This gives the NSX ballistic pick-up at any speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.20,0:09:05.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,看 瞬间的推力 太美妙了\N{\fs90}Look, instant shove. It's lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.51,0:09:15.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,但前面的两个电机才是真的主角\N{\fs90}But it's the two at the front that are the real party-piece
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.83,0:09:18.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它们完全独立地\N{\fs90}because they drive a wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.07,0:09:20.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,驱动两边的轮子\N{\fs90}each totally independently of each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.19,0:09:22.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,这意味着它有着\N{\fs90}Which means this car has
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.22,0:09:25.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,和宇宙飞船一样先进的四驱系统\N{\fs90}a sort of space-age four-wheel drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.06,0:09:29.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以在入弯时\N{\fs90}And that means extraordinary things happen
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.61,0:09:31.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,也就带来了不可思议的表现\N{\fs90}when you throw it into a corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.01,0:09:40.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,比如你接近这个弯角时\N{\fs90}So, as you approach a corner like this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.38,0:09:42.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,车载电脑会计算车速\N{\fs90}computers are measuring the speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.21,0:09:45.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,检测G力 转向角 等等\N{\fs90}they're measuring G-force, steering input, and so forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.98,0:09:47.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,它会根据需要 配给车轮额外的动力\N{\fs90}They're adding power to the wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.70,0:09:49.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,或减少部分动力\N{\fs90}or taking power away from the wheel as it's needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.32,0:09:54.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后你就能平稳 可控地过弯\N{\fs90}Then you get perfectly flat, perfectly controlled corners.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.79,0:09:58.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,有点像开本田思域\N{\fs90}It is a bit like driving a Honda Civic!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.60,0:10:02.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,有人会说\N{\fs90}There are people who would say
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.50,0:10:04.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,给车配备了这样的科技\N{\fs90}that technology like this in a car,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.76,0:10:07.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,让它变得更安全也更无趣了\N{\fs90}helping it feel secure, will make it dull.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.23,0:10:08.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我并不觉得无趣\N{\fs90}But it doesn't feel dull to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.76,0:10:10.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,只觉得惊艳\N{\fs90}It feels tremendous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.64,0:10:14.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能轻松地高速行驶\N{\fs90}I'm going fast and I'm relaxing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.84,0:10:16.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,这有什么不好\N{\fs90}What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.08,0:10:21.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这个未来感十足的四轮驱动\N{\fs90}But the futuristic four-wheel drive
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.58,0:10:24.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是NSX上唯一\N{\fs90}isn't the only piece of 23rd-century engineering
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.03,0:10:26.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,来自23世纪的产物\N{\fs90}on the NSX.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.47,0:10:29.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,气动特性就非常巧妙\N{\fs90}The aerodynamics, for example, are so clever,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.79,0:10:31.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,它可以冷却所有的电机\N{\fs90}they can cool all the motors
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.65,0:10:35.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,同时还能提供大量下压力\N{\fs90}while providing vast amounts of grip-enhancing downforce
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.45,0:10:39.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,增加前后轮的抓地力\N{\fs90}to the front and rear wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.87,0:10:42.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,无需传统的尾翼和扰流板\N{\fs90}And it does all this without anything
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.41,0:10:46.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,它就能做到这些\N{\fs90}as old-fashioned as huge wings and spoilers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.79,0:11:01.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,不仅是因为这些激动人心的科技\N{\fs90}It's not just the technology, which is brilliant,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.25,0:11:03.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,而是这些科技都与车融为一体\N{\fs90}it's that that technology is on this car
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.03,0:11:05.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 我们有混动超跑\N{\fs90}Yes, we have hybrid supercars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.92,0:11:08.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们有LaFerrari 迈凯伦P1\N{\fs90}We have the LaFerrari, the McLaren P1,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.61,0:11:09.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,保时捷918\N{\fs90}the Porsche 918.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.63,0:11:11.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是这些都要数百万\N{\fs90}But they're in the million-pound bracket.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.37,0:11:15.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,NSX的价格只有LaFerrari的八分之一\N{\fs90}This is only an eighth of the price of the LaFerrari,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.30,0:11:17.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,且NSX的设计更精妙\N{\fs90}and it's actually cleverer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.54,0:11:20.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,我爱这辆车\N{\fs90}I love this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.67,0:11:23.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,我爱它的外观 我爱它的声音\N{\fs90}I love the way it looks. I love the sounds it makes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.23,0:11:26.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这复杂精巧的混动系统\N{\fs90}I like the sophistication of the hybrid drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:27.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,我喜欢它的性能\N{\fs90}I like the performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.50,0:11:30.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,我喜欢它的转向操控 还有这内饰\N{\fs90}I like the steering. I like the interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.28,0:11:31.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,我真的很喜欢它\N{\fs90}I really, really like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.79,0:11:34.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,我发现自己按捺不住地想入手一辆\N{\fs90}And I find myself wanting one quite badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.29,0:11:41.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,初代NSX让人们可以\N{\fs90}The original NSX made owning a supercar
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.34,0:11:43.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,用低廉的价格拥有一辆舒适的超跑\N{\fs90}less painful and less expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.83,0:11:49.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,这代混动超跑也一样\N{\fs90}This has done the same for the hybrid supercar.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.20,0:11:52.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,它的确是名合格的继承者\N{\fs90}It really is a worthy successor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.42,0:12:07.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 本田\N{\fs90}James, Honda...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.35,0:12:11.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,本田花了十年时间研发这车\N{\fs90}Honda took ten years to develop that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.23,0:12:12.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后呢\N{\fs90}And?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.34,0:12:14.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,造辆车 用十年\N{\fs90}Ten years is an enormous amount of time
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.98,0:12:15.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,太过了\N{\fs90}to do a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.63,0:12:17.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,你不能因为花的时间太长\N{\fs90}You can't criticise something
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.38,0:12:19.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,就批评它\N{\fs90}because people spent too long on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.54,0:12:22.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,没人会说 我不去参观科隆大教堂\N{\fs90}People aren't gonna say "I'm not gonna look round Cologne cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.41,0:12:24.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,这花了600年才建好"\N{\fs90}They took 600 years to build it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.17,0:12:28.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,总之 我爱这辆车\N{\fs90}Anyway, I love it. I love that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.38,0:12:30.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管怎样 我们已经听完\N{\fs90}Anyway, look, we've heard
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.36,0:12:31.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,你对NSX的评价了\N{\fs90}what you've got to say about the NSX.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.83,0:12:33.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在要把它移交给这个人\N{\fs90}Now it's time to hand it over
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.65,0:12:35.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,他觉得\N{\fs90}to a man who thinks that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.12,0:12:37.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,盆栽植物是共产主义的阴谋\N{\fs90}Well, potted plants are a Communist plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.02,0:12:40.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 有请老美\N{\fs90}Yep. Here he comes. It's the American!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.29,0:12:49.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,英国 天气糟心 啤酒糟心\N{\fs90}Come to England. Shit weather. Shit beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.46,0:12:51.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,他出发了\N{\fs90}And he's off!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.53,0:12:53.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,明显兴致高昂\N{\fs90}Clearly in a tremendous mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.94,0:12:56.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,但路面非常潮湿\N{\fs90}But it is very wet out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.57,0:12:58.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,他一脚油门进入不直道时\N{\fs90}Wipers flapping away
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.61,0:13:01.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,雨刮在狂甩\N{\fs90}as he powers onto the Isn't Straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.28,0:13:02.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,看起来不错\N{\fs90}Looking good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.64,0:13:03.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我老家\N{\fs90}Where I come from,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.95,0:13:06.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,这玩意儿的标志就是"不精准" (ACURA原意"精准")\N{\fs90}this thing's badge is inaccurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.08,0:13:08.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,有点像屌丝才开的凯迪拉克\N{\fs90}Kind of like a loser's Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.61,0:13:10.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,奇怪的是 我们还在等\N{\fs90}And yet, strangely, we're still waiting
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.63,0:13:12.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,凯迪拉克的混动超跑上市\N{\fs90}for Cadillac's hybrid supercar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.92,0:13:15.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 飞驰进入留你名弯\N{\fs90}Right, now, flying into Your Name Here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.90,0:13:18.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,今天真适合开四驱车\N{\fs90}this really is a good day to have four-wheel drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.52,0:13:20.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,我相信就算是老美\N{\fs90}I'm sure even the American can appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.96,0:13:23.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,也会赞赏本田的高科技\N{\fs90}the Honda's hi-tech features.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.16,0:13:25.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是啥外太空玩意\N{\fs90}What is this Space Invaders shit?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.77,0:13:27.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,当我没说\N{\fs90}Clearly not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.40,0:13:30.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,地板油再次通过不直道\N{\fs90}Right, full power for the Isn't again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.77,0:13:34.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,电不该用在引擎上 那是给车灯和座椅用的\N{\fs90}Electric ain't for engines. It's for lights and chairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.28,0:13:37.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,他确实有点落伍\N{\fs90}He is not a modern man, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.14,0:13:39.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 划过一片水潭\N{\fs90}Right, carving through the standing water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.58,0:13:41.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,进入老奶房弯\N{\fs90}Into Old Lady's House.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.55,0:13:43.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,略微有点滑\N{\fs90}Slithering about a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.38,0:13:46.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在他飞速驶过颠簸路段\N{\fs90}Now he's leaning on it for the Unsettled section.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.82,0:13:49.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,过了机库 到了变电箱弯\N{\fs90}Past the hangars and up to Sub Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.79,0:13:52.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,大力猛踩电子刹车\N{\fs90}Hard on those wi-fi brakes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.21,0:13:53.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,减速过倒数第二个弯\N{\fs90}for the second-to-last corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.90,0:13:56.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里他要怎么过呢\N{\fs90}How's he gonna manage through here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.06,0:13:58.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 走线靠外 略微动力不足\N{\fs90}Yes, stepping out a bit under power.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.38,0:13:59.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,通过绵羊坡\N{\fs90}Through Field Of Sheep,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.01,0:14:02.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,走线很紧 穿过终点\N{\fs90}keeping it tidy through there, and across the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.71,0:14:13.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\fs90}Right,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.82,0:14:18.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看NSX在圈速榜上排名如何\N{\fs90}let's see now where the NSX goes on our lap board.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.67,0:14:20.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们来看看\N{\fs90}Let's have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.21,0:14:25.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的天 詹姆斯\N{\fs90}Oh, dear, James.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.86,0:14:31.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯\N{\fs90}James.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.50,0:14:35.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,你怎么不告诉我们它这么慢\N{\fs90}Why didn't you tell us it was very slow?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.63,0:14:39.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是因为跑道太湿了  -等等\N{\fs90}- It's streaming wet! - So hang on a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.24,0:14:42.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,来自乌龟的测评加上湿圈速\N{\fs90}We've had a review from a tortoise and a wet lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.74,0:14:45.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以这都是白费功夫了\N{\fs90}Which means we've learnt precisely nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.74,0:14:48.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,恩 是的\N{\fs90}Um... Yeah, you're right. Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.25,0:14:49.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,-白费功夫了  -好的我们继续\N{\fs90}- Nothing at all. - So let's move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:54.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,好 让我们往售票机里投币\N{\fs90}Yes, let's do that by popping some loose change in the ticket machine
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.22,0:14:57.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,在唠嗑街上停会儿车\N{\fs90}so we can park awhile on Conversation Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.50,0:15:07.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在\N{\fs90}OK, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.87,0:15:09.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我有话要说  -很好\N{\fs90}- I've got some conversation. - Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.87,0:15:13.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,昨天半夜 斯图加特有天气警报\N{\fs90}Last night at midnight, there was alarm in Stuttgart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.01,0:15:16.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,当地的执政党 绿党\N{\fs90}The Green Party that runs the city
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.48,0:15:21.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,建议居民不要使用烧柴的炉子\N{\fs90}asked everyone here not to use wood-burning stoves
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.41,0:15:23.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且今天不要开车\N{\fs90}and not to drive their car today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.89,0:15:26.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,-为什么  -因为雾霾\N{\fs90}- Why? - Because of the smog.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.13,0:15:33.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,我是瞎编的吗\N{\fs90}Am I making this up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.33,0:15:35.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,证据在这\N{\fs90}There it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.67,0:15:41.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有什么\N{\fs90}I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.47,0:15:43.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,比这更清楚了\N{\fs90}I can't imagine anything clearer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.96,0:15:46.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,这空气透亮的和琴酒一样\N{\fs90}That is... That is gin-clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.38,0:15:47.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是据绿党所说\N{\fs90}but according to the Green Party...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.67,0:15:48.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,我真没瞎说\N{\fs90}I'm not making this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.81,0:15:49.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们都是斯图加特人 对吧\N{\fs90}You're all from Stuttgart, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.01,0:15:51.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,今天的天气报警\N{\fs90}There is an alarm today
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.45,0:15:54.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是因为雾霾吧  -是的\N{\fs90}- because of the smog. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.28,0:15:56.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,在哪儿呢\N{\fs90}Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.16,0:15:59.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,天气好的时候 还能更透亮吗\N{\fs90}How clear is it on a good day?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.12,0:16:03.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,这有张北京的照片\N{\fs90}We've got a photograph here of Beijing on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.72,0:16:05.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们来对比一下\N{\fs90}Let us compare and contrast
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.03,0:16:09.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,北京的雾霾天和斯图加特的\N{\fs90}Beijing on a smoggy day with Stuttgart on a...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.10,0:16:10.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不一样吧  -雾霾天\N{\fs90}- Not the same. - ...a smoggy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.83,0:16:13.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,我就问一下 如果绿党真的禁止开车\N{\fs90}Can I just ask, what would you have done
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.37,0:16:16.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们要怎么做\N{\fs90}if they'd have actually ordered you not to drive cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.30,0:16:17.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在这只是个倡议\N{\fs90}At the moment, it's an advisory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.83,0:16:19.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果他们说禁止开车\N{\fs90}If they said you are banned from driving cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.65,0:16:21.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们怎么办\N{\fs90}what would you have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.48,0:16:24.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,乘火车过来 无法想象\N{\fs90}Come on the train? That's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.78,0:16:25.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,但事实是\N{\fs90}But this is the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.94,0:16:27.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们不懂德国人\N{\fs90}that we don't really understand about Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.72,0:16:29.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,规矩就是规矩\N{\fs90}Once something becomes a rule, it is a rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.02,0:16:32.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,有一次我和两个朋友\N{\fs90}I once had a very interesting conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.61,0:16:33.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,进行了一次有趣的交谈\N{\fs90}with two friends of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.50,0:16:35.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,一个是加州来的 另一个是德国人\N{\fs90}One is from California and one is from Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.79,0:16:38.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在讨论 驾照丢了怎么办\N{\fs90}We were talking about losing your driving licence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.65,0:16:41.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,加州人问 在德国 如果驾照丢了\N{\fs90}The Californian said, "In Germany, what would happen
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.98,0:16:44.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,开车会怎样\N{\fs90}if you lost your licence and then you drove your car?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.96,0:16:46.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,德国人说 不 你不能这么做\N{\fs90}The German said, "No, you cannot do this."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.34,0:16:51.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,他说 这不应该\N{\fs90}He says, "I know you're not supposed to,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.38,0:16:52.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,但假如你开了呢\N{\fs90}but what if you did?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.70,0:16:55.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,德国人说 不 你不能开 你没驾照\N{\fs90}He said, "No. You cannot drive. You have no licence."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.38,0:16:58.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,加州人说 我知道\N{\fs90}The Californian went, "Yeah, man,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.27,0:16:59.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,但某天晚上 你就是\N{\fs90}but late one night, you just...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.68,0:17:01.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,控制不住地开了车\N{\fs90}hell, you go for a drive."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.38,0:17:03.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,德国人说\N{\fs90}The German went, "It is impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.21,0:17:04.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有驾照就不可能开车\N{\fs90}to drive without a licence!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.76,0:17:06.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不可能  -不可能\N{\fs90}- Impossible! - Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.23,0:17:14.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,我发现了一件有趣的事\N{\fs90}There's an interesting thing I discovered here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.96,0:17:18.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,在高速上 你想开多快都行\N{\fs90}On a motorway, obviously you can drive as fast as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.70,0:17:20.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,但就有人 虽然不常见\N{\fs90}You get people sometimes, not often,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.32,0:17:22.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你们的变线纪律太严格了\N{\fs90}cos your lane discipline is unbelievable,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.18,0:17:25.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,但就有人在快车道上慢吞吞地爬\N{\fs90}but sometimes they sit in the outside lane just dawdling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.44,0:17:29.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你在后面跟车 我这有处罚条例\N{\fs90}If you tailgate them... OK? I've got the fines here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.36,0:17:33.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,你要付400欧的罚款 记2分\N{\fs90}You get a 400 euro fine, two penalty points,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.34,0:17:36.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且三个月内禁止跟车\N{\fs90}and a three-month ban for tailgating.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.10,0:17:37.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这真是极刑啊 太狠了  -是的\N{\fs90}- That is extreme. Ouch! - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.02,0:17:39.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,但如果你从内侧超车\N{\fs90}But if you overtake them on the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.92,0:17:41.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,从内车道上超过他们\N{\fs90}just go past them on the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.43,0:17:44.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是150欧罚款 记1分\N{\fs90}that's a 150 euro fine, and one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.45,0:17:45.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个不错\N{\fs90}Well, there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.27,0:17:48.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,等等 高潮来了\N{\fs90}No. This is where it gets really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.03,0:17:52.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你从路肩超车 也就是紧急停车带\N{\fs90}If you go on the hard shoulder to overtake, the emergency lane,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.20,0:17:56.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,也是记1分 但是只有90欧罚款\N{\fs90}that's also one point but only a 90 euro fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.57,0:17:59.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,找到正解了 就这么办\N{\fs90}There's your answer. That's what you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.87,0:18:01.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,不行\N{\fs90}No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.64,0:18:07.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,等等 你以为这就完了吗\N{\fs90}No, because... Aha. You may think that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.87,0:18:10.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你给车装上蓝色的灯\N{\fs90}But if you fit your car with blue lights,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.23,0:18:11.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,那种蓝色的闪灯\N{\fs90}flashing blue lights, basically,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.67,0:18:13.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,你基本就把车改成了警车\N{\fs90}you turn you car into a police car,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.55,0:18:16.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我看看处罚条例\N{\fs90}you get... I've got the point fines here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.78,0:18:19.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,你将罚款20欧 不记分\N{\fs90}20 euro fine and no points at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.53,0:18:23.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,你在逗我吗\N{\fs90}What? You're joking!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.46,0:18:27.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你不懂  -这是真的\N{\fs90}- No, you don't understand. - That is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.60,0:18:30.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,这听上去不合理\N{\fs90}That is very strange to our ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.30,0:18:32.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为如果你在英国这么干的话\N{\fs90}Cos if you tried that at home in the UK,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.94,0:18:35.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,你将被控 假扮警察\N{\fs90}you would be charged with impersonating a police officer,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.76,0:18:38.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,你这辈子都别想从监狱里出来了\N{\fs90}and you would never get out of prison, ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.78,0:18:41.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,人们常说德国人缺乏幽默细胞\N{\fs90}People say Germans have no sense of humour.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.81,0:18:43.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你想知道什么叫不幽默\N{\fs90}If you want to know what no sense of humour is,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.65,0:18:45.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,来英国 假扮个警察试试\N{\fs90}impersonate a policeman in Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.65,0:18:47.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,你就知道什么叫做一点也不幽默了\N{\fs90}Then you'll know what no sense of humour is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.76,0:18:51.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,好啦 我们今天的唠嗑街就到这里了\N{\fs90}Right, that is the end of Conversation Straße.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.76,0:18:58.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们都喜欢 SUV 的概念\N{\fs90}We all like the idea of a sports utility vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.81,0:19:01.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,一台车 在周末 足够应付澳大利亚内陆沙漠\N{\fs90}A car that can handle the Australian outback at the weekend
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.67,0:19:05.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,在周一早上 又能去霍根海姆赛道上刷个新的最快圈速\N{\fs90}and then set a new lap record at Hockenheim on a Monday morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.97,0:19:08.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是就连德国的车厂\N{\fs90}But even the German car-makers
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.64,0:19:10.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,好想都不能把这个概念玩顺溜\N{\fs90}can't seem to make the concept work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.55,0:19:13.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是奥迪的产品 RS Q3\N{\fs90}We've got this from Audi. The RS Q3.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.07,0:19:14.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,车不怎么样\N{\fs90}Which is a dismal car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.52,0:19:17.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,宝马也推出了X4 我记得是这个名字\N{\fs90}BMW have the X4, I think that's called.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.81,0:19:18.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我哪个都不喜欢\N{\fs90}Don't want one of those, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.04,0:19:21.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,奔驰也有这个吓人的大魔头\N{\fs90}Mercedes have this horrible monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.52,0:19:23.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们都很垃圾\N{\fs90}They're all just rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.59,0:19:26.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我猜猜 你有个办法\N{\fs90}And let me guess. You have a solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.41,0:19:27.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,-可不是么 -天啊\N{\fs90}- Yes, I do. - Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.84,0:19:29.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,我当然有了 有那么一台车\N{\fs90}Yes, I do. A car
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.87,0:19:32.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,应该既运动又多功能\N{\fs90}that is both sporty and utilitarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.77,0:19:34.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,这下好看了\N{\fs90}This will be good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.20,0:19:36.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,你心一点都不诚 看好了\N{\fs90}Ye of little faith. Watch this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.14,0:19:42.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一台路虎发现\N{\fs90}This is a Land Rover Discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.04,0:19:44.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,在英国泥泞的南部\N{\fs90}doing utilitarian things
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.98,0:19:47.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,做着功能性的事情\N{\fs90}in Britain's muddy underbelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.72,0:19:52.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,一台像这样的机器 很明显\N{\fs90}And obviously a machine like this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.84,0:19:57.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,不可能被改造成一台跑车\N{\fs90}cannot possibly be converted into a sports car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.29,0:20:01.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的么\N{\fs90}Or can it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.56,0:20:07.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,首先 你得把这非常丑的车身拆下来\N{\fs90}First of all, we have to remove this rather ungainly body.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.04,0:20:10.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是现代的汽车你就没法这么拆\N{\fs90}You can't do that with a modern car
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.32,0:20:12.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为车身本身就是底盘 是承力的骨架\N{\fs90}because the body is the chassis. It's the skeleton.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.01,0:20:15.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你把底盘卸了 你除了一堆没法装上去的配件外\N{\fs90}If you take it away, you're left with nothing more
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.44,0:20:17.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么都没有了\N{\fs90}than a collection of unjoined-up parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.98,0:20:20.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而 你可以把车身像这样\N{\fs90}However, you can remove the body
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.58,0:20:21.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,从一台发现上卸下来\N{\fs90}on an old Discovery like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.01,0:20:24.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,用的工具不会比这更多了\N{\fs90}using nothing more than one of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.36,0:20:33.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,仅仅过了40分钟\N{\fs90}After just 40 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.81,0:20:35.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,在没人帮忙的情况下\N{\fs90}with no help from anyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.46,0:20:38.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我把车变成了这样\N{\fs90}I ended up with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.74,0:20:47.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,很显然 它依然是多功能的\N{\fs90}Obviously it's still utilitarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.55,0:20:49.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,它依然可以趟过河流\N{\fs90}It will still wade through rivers
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.81,0:20:52.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且缓缓爬上泥泞的河岸\N{\fs90}and crawl its way up muddy banks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.38,0:20:54.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是现在\N{\fs90}But now there's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.42,0:20:56.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,开始有了丝丝运动的味道\N{\fs90}a sporty flavour as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.05,0:21:03.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,在移除了沉重的车身后 它开起来灵活敏捷又轻盈\N{\fs90}Without the heavy body, it feels nimble, agile, light.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.93,0:21:11.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,要不是风挡是那么接近我的脸\N{\fs90}If it weren't for the fact that the windscreen is now very close to my face,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.60,0:21:14.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,我都会以为这是一台兰博基尼盖拉多\N{\fs90}it would feel like a Lamborghini Gallardo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:20.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,这东西真正的问题在于\N{\fs90}The only real problem with this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.12,0:21:22.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,英国是一个受警察管制的国家\N{\fs90}is that Britain is a police state,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.58,0:21:24.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我开着这玩意儿上路\N{\fs90}and if I took this on a public road,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.41,0:21:26.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我马上就会被警察截停\N{\fs90}I'd be stopped immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.61,0:21:29.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,警察会告诉我\N{\fs90}by the constabulary who would point out
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.12,0:21:30.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,我将会违反大概\N{\fs90}that I was contravening about...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.85,0:21:34.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,4870条不同的法条\N{\fs90}4,870 different laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.99,0:21:40.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然 也不暖和\N{\fs90}It's not warm, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.50,0:21:43.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 不 这太蠢了\N{\fs90}Oh, no, that's stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.86,0:21:46.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,让人欣慰的是 把它移植上一个跑车的车身\N{\fs90}Happily, both these problems would be solved
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.52,0:21:49.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,这些问题都可以解决\N{\fs90}when I fitted it with the body from a sports car.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.14,0:21:56.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是我要找的跑车\N{\fs90}And this is the sports car I've gone for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.04,0:22:00.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,一台1978年的MGB\N{\fs90}A 1978 MGB.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.52,0:22:07.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,手法熟练的技师开始剥去她的肌肤\N{\fs90}Highly-trained men are now removing its skin
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.84,0:22:09.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,并在稍后 通过一场两小时的复杂手术\N{\fs90}which will then be mated
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.42,0:22:11.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,将其覆于\N{\fs90}in a delicate two-hour operation...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.69,0:22:15.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,那台充满泥土气息的\N{\fs90}...to the internal organs
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.93,0:22:17.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,V8发现的内部器官之上\N{\fs90}of the mud-plugging V8.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.37,0:22:21.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,第二天早上\N{\fs90}The following morning
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.50,0:22:23.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,我无与伦比的车已经准备好了\N{\fs90}my incredible car was ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.32,0:22:37.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车简直美极了\N{\fs90}It is incredible
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.08,0:22:40.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,就在公棚里 我造就了这样的一台机器\N{\fs90}that in a shed I have created something which has...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.92,0:22:45.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,破解了汽车业界中 车型该如何跨界混合的谜题\N{\fs90}eluded the combined might of the motor industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.86,0:22:50.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一台真正的 SUV\N{\fs90}It is a proper sports utility vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.44,0:22:52.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我许之以 MGD 之名\N{\fs90}I call it the MGD,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.27,0:22:54.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在我就要看看\N{\fs90}and now I'm going to find out
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.59,0:22:56.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,它在路上的表现如何\N{\fs90}how well it works on a road.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.94,0:23:10.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,太棒了\N{\fs90}This is... magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.39,0:23:16.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,这家伙太快了\N{\fs90}And it is quick. Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.76,0:23:20.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了展示其速度\N{\fs90}To demonstrate just how quick,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.91,0:23:22.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,我将来场加速赛\N{\fs90}I'm going to do a drag race
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.52,0:23:26.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,对抗汽车行业所设计的SUV\N{\fs90}against the motor industry's idea of an SUV.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.45,0:23:34.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,方向盘有点虚位\N{\fs90}Little bit of play there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.41,0:23:40.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,开始吧\N{\fs90}Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.70,0:23:46.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,走起 看啊\N{\fs90}Come on! Yes, look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.34,0:23:51.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,这1.5升的柴油车\N{\fs90}The 1.5-litre diesel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.79,0:23:58.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,无法和3.9升 V8的MGD媲美\N{\fs90}is no match for the 3.9-litre V8 MGD.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.94,0:24:02.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,加把劲 大英帝国的骄傲\N{\fs90}Come on, Pride of Britain!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.61,0:24:05.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,赢啦\N{\fs90}Yes! Ha-ha-ha-ha-ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.51,0:24:10.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,不好\N{\fs90}Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.27,0:24:12.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,刹车失灵了\N{\fs90}The brakes don't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.74,0:24:19.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,在确信性能表现优异后\N{\fs90}With the performance box ticked,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.87,0:24:21.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,我继续测评\N{\fs90}I continued my testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.46,0:24:26.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,MGD在很多方面都让我想起\N{\fs90}In many ways, the MGD puts me in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.23,0:24:28.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,奥迪R8敞篷版\N{\fs90}of an Audi R8 Spyder.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.70,0:24:32.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然 奥迪的仪表盘肯定不会出问题\N{\fs90}I mean, OK, in the Audi, the dials would work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.06,0:24:35.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,以及开关 刹车\N{\fs90}And the  switches. And the brakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.31,0:24:37.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有转向\N{\fs90}And the steering.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.82,0:24:39.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且不会这么抖 但是\N{\fs90}And it's a bit less bouncy, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.66,0:24:41.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,这俩车\N{\fs90}both of them
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.08,0:24:44.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,都是四驱两座\N{\fs90}are four-wheel-drive, two-seater,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.78,0:24:46.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,敞篷的V8\N{\fs90}drop-head V8s.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.58,0:24:49.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然 这两者\N{\fs90}There is, however, one very big difference
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.72,0:24:51.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,也有一点迥然不同\N{\fs90}between the two cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.22,0:24:53.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,开奥迪可干不了这事\N{\fs90}You can't do this in an Audi.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.72,0:25:02.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,太棒了\N{\fs90}Oh, yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.31,0:25:08.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,不久之前 我还在跑道上驰骋\N{\fs90}Moments ago I was haring round a handling track,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.31,0:25:09.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,看如今\N{\fs90}and now look.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.02,0:25:12.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,简直惊为天人\N{\fs90}It's brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.72,0:25:19.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,别现在罢工啊 这个小崽子\N{\fs90}Oh, no! Not now, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.23,0:25:21.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,不对 这个小冤家\N{\fs90}I mean, you wonderful thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.52,0:25:24.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,阻风门出问题了\N{\fs90}Choke. Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.77,0:25:26.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,完蛋\N{\fs90}Yeah, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.42,0:25:31.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,它苟延残喘了\N{\fs90}It's on its shutdown thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.77,0:25:32.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了省油\N{\fs90}It's just to save fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.86,0:25:34.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,它偶尔只用两缸工作\N{\fs90}it goes on two cylinders sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.80,0:25:40.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,等引擎管理的玩意\N{\fs90}Once the engine management thingy had run its...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.87,0:25:42.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,完成诊断程序后\N{\fs90}diagnostic program,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.68,0:25:44.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,我再次出发\N{\fs90}I was back on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.22,0:25:45.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,走着\N{\fs90}Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.66,0:25:50.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\fs90}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.77,0:25:55.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,强大的四驱系统把我送上那的\N{\fs90}Mighty four-wheel-drive system hauling me up that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.28,0:25:57.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么鬼\N{\fs90}What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.76,0:26:01.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,赶紧停车\N{\fs90}I'm stopping. Stopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.24,0:26:09.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,天 这看来不太对劲呢\N{\fs90}Oh, Lord, that is not right, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.67,0:26:19.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,再次发动后\N{\fs90}As I got going for the second time,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.54,0:26:21.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,我被自己蠢到了\N{\fs90}I realised I'd been a bit of a chump.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.59,0:26:24.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的错误在于\N{\fs90}The mistake I've made, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.24,0:26:26.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,在向你们介绍这车前\N{\fs90}is that I've introduced you to this car
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.80,0:26:28.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,我并未真的路测过\N{\fs90}before I've really tested it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.23,0:26:29.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,汽车制造商可不能这样\N{\fs90}That's not what car-makers do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.85,0:26:32.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们一般先试车\N{\fs90}They test a car and then show it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.50,0:26:34.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,再向媒体和大众展示\N{\fs90}to the press and the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.63,0:26:37.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,我本末倒置了\N{\fs90}I'm doing that the other way round.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.12,0:26:38.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,我没测试\N{\fs90}I'm introducing this to you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.37,0:26:40.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,就向你们介绍这车了\N{\fs90}before I've done the testing and...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.30,0:26:47.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的天\N{\fs90}Oh, for Christ's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.69,0:26:52.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,你个磨人的小妖精\N{\fs90}You little beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.91,0:27:01.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,刚说到哪了\N{\fs90}Er, now, yes, what was I saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.17,0:27:07.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,问题在于 你们在看的是我的工作过程\N{\fs90}I think the issue is really you're watching my workings-out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.42,0:27:11.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,而你们真正想看的是成品\N{\fs90}What you really want to see is the finished product.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.35,0:27:12.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,我应该给你们看成品\N{\fs90}That's what I should have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.70,0:27:15.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,天\N{\fs90}Oh, Christ's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.28,0:27:18.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\fs90}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.33,0:27:24.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,至此 毫无由来的 我决定\N{\fs90}At this point, I decided, for no particular reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.42,0:27:26.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,打消MG这个主意\N{\fs90}to scrap the MG idea
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.84,0:27:28.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,另找别的灵感\N{\fs90}and go for something else instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.28,0:27:34.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是我的选择\N{\fs90}This is what I chose.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.41,0:27:37.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,1980年款奔驰SL\N{\fs90}A 1980s Mercedes SL.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.54,0:27:40.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,从一定程度上 它是\N{\fs90}Partly because it's the very essence
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.32,0:27:42.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,安静 城市需求\N{\fs90}of quiet, urban restraint,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.43,0:27:43.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,品味与优雅的精髓\N{\fs90}taste and elegance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.98,0:27:47.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,它是鲍比尤因在达拉斯开的车\N{\fs90}It's a car that was driven by Bobby Ewing in Dallas.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.16,0:27:50.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,主要地 我选它因为\N{\fs90}Mostly, though, I chose it because
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.50,0:27:53.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,它与路虎发现的底盘能更好契合\N{\fs90}it would fit more snugly on the Discovery chassis.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.90,0:27:59.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个时候 这个孜孜不倦工作了\N{\fs90}This time, the men worked tirelessly
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.56,0:28:01.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,将近一天的男人们\N{\fs90}for nearly a whole day
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.27,0:28:02.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,来合璧这两辆车\N{\fs90}to marry the two cars
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.58,0:28:05.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,而结果十分惊人\N{\fs90}and the result was spectacular.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.78,0:28:12.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一辆车让我无可非议地给它命名为\N{\fs90}It's a car I have justifiably called...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.42,0:28:14.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,卓越\N{\fs90}The Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.06,0:28:18.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,它的脏腑来自于路虎发现\N{\fs90}The internal organs from a Landrover Discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.50,0:28:23.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,套上了迷人的奔驰SL美丽的皮囊\N{\fs90}mated to the beautiful skin of a glamorous Mercedes SL.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.76,0:28:25.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,来创造一个纯粹的版本\N{\fs90}To create a vision of pure...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.83,0:28:28.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,那个词是什么来着\N{\fs90}What's the word?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.23,0:28:31.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,-垃圾 -这才不是垃圾\N{\fs90}- Rubbish. - It's not rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.16,0:28:34.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,你用刷子还是水桶给它涂的漆\N{\fs90}Did you paint it with a brush or a bucket?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.16,0:28:36.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,它的头灯在你拐弯的时候还会转\N{\fs90}It's got those headlights that swivel when you go round a bend.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.98,0:28:38.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以他们指着路\N{\fs90}So they point at the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.68,0:28:40.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,好 让我这样问你\N{\fs90}OK, let me ask you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.81,0:28:41.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,你更想要哪个\N{\fs90}Which would you rather have?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.78,0:28:43.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,卓越还是保时捷\N{\fs90}The Excellent or that Porsche?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.72,0:28:45.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,-那台保时捷 -为什么\N{\fs90}- That Porsche. - Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.85,0:28:48.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它在每个方面都比较好\N{\fs90}Because it's better in every single way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.96,0:28:51.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了证明我那些冷嘲热讽的同事们是错的\N{\fs90}To prove my cynical colleagues wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.70,0:28:53.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,我邀请他们来兜一圈\N{\fs90}I invited them to go for a drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.03,0:28:57.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦不错\N{\fs90}Oh, kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.43,0:29:00.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,看到了没 这是一个为矮个子男士提供的选件\N{\fs90}See? It's an optional extra for the shorter gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.57,0:29:03.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你舒服吗 哈蒙德 -不\N{\fs90}- Are you comfy, Hammond? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.24,0:29:05.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我就只能坐进去这么一点吗  -是的\N{\fs90}- Is this as in as I can get? - Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.11,0:29:10.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,好 听这个\N{\fs90}Right, listen to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.71,0:29:13.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦不 它开了\N{\fs90}Oh, no, it moves!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.52,0:29:20.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们只开了几公里 哈蒙德和船长\N{\fs90}We'd only gone a few miles before Richard and James
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.98,0:29:22.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,就彻底改变了主意\N{\fs90}completely changed their minds
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.92,0:29:25.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后意识到 卓越是他们坐过\N{\fs90}and realised that The Excellent was the best car
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.56,0:29:27.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,最好的车\N{\fs90}they'd ever been in.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.19,0:29:29.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 我们才没有 别在画外音里\N{\fs90}No, we haven't. Stop saying things
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.21,0:29:30.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,说些子虚乌有的事情\N{\fs90}in voiceover that aren't true.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.72,0:29:32.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,我还以为你改变主意了\N{\fs90}I thought you'd changed your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.43,0:29:34.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 也许有一点 这比我想的还要差\N{\fs90}No! Maybe a bit. It's worse than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.98,0:29:37.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我能把加热器打开吗 -那个还没有连上\N{\fs90}- Can I put the heater on? - That's not connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.74,0:29:38.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,-它没有 -没有\N{\fs90}- Is it not? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.07,0:29:41.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,-下面那个刻度盘是什么 -车速表\N{\fs90}- What's that dial down there? - Speedometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.70,0:29:43.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么你要用这个 不用那个\N{\fs90}Why have you got that one, not that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.38,0:29:45.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,-那个用不了 -它有油量表吗\N{\fs90}- That doesn't work. - Has it got a fuel gauge?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.78,0:29:48.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没有那些 -它有温度计吗\N{\fs90}- Not as such. - Has it got a temperature gauge?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.65,0:29:49.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,并没有\N{\fs90}Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.47,0:29:51.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,有这么多线露在外面\N{\fs90}There's a lot of wires hanging out of the dash
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.45,0:29:52.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们都没有连接东西\N{\fs90}that aren't connected to things.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.89,0:29:54.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,你都没有给它内饰\N{\fs90}You haven't given it an interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.29,0:30:00.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我可以看到路 -我也能\N{\fs90}- I can see the road. - I can as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.85,0:30:03.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 地板上有个洞\N{\fs90}No, there's a hole in the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.06,0:30:07.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,让哈蒙德和梅在纠结些细枝末节的问题时\N{\fs90}While Hammond and May had one or two minor issues,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.47,0:30:10.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们都同意 如果我把我的车投产\N{\fs90}they both agreed that if I were to put my car into production,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.74,0:30:13.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,它会让我大赚一笔\N{\fs90}it would make me a fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.21,0:30:15.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 我们也没有同意那个\N{\fs90}No, we didn't agree to that, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.48,0:30:17.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,看 我做了一点算是 说真的\N{\fs90}Look, I've done the maths. Honestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.94,0:30:19.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,发现要2500英镑\N{\fs90}The Discovery was £2,500.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.55,0:30:23.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,奔驰要4500英镑 改造要7000英镑\N{\fs90}Mercedes £4,500. £7,000 for the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.58,0:30:27.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,一共是14000英镑 -我可以以120000英镑的价钱把它卖了\N{\fs90}That's 14,000 quid. I could sell this for £120,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.41,0:30:28.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不 你做不到  -我可以做到\N{\fs90}- No, you couldn't. - Yes, I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.89,0:30:31.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,卡宴turbo是120\N{\fs90}A Cayenne Turbo is 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.14,0:30:35.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,卡宴turbo是保时捷打造的好车\N{\fs90}A Cayenne Turbo is a proper car built by Porsche.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.10,0:30:38.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,这只是一个蠢货把两辆废车拼在一起\N{\fs90}This is two scrap cars glued together by a Muppet.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.77,0:30:41.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,它不是为你这种人设计的\N{\fs90}It isn't designed for people like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.21,0:30:42.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么人 有眼睛的人\N{\fs90}What, people with eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.98,0:30:45.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,可以早上自己穿衣服的人\N{\fs90}People who can dress themselves in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.81,0:30:48.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我会明确的告诉你谁会买这个车\N{\fs90}I'll tell you exactly who will buy this car.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.25,0:30:50.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,用圆尾剪刀的人\N{\fs90}People who use roundy-ended scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.58,0:30:52.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,足球选手\N{\fs90}Footballers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.11,0:30:54.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他们不会 -球员们喜欢法拉利\N{\fs90}- No, they won't. - Footballers like Ferraris.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.74,0:30:56.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 还有宾利和路虎\N{\fs90}Yeah, and Bentleys and Range Rovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.70,0:30:58.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,-还有阿斯顿马丁 -才不是这个东西\N{\fs90}- And Aston Martins. - Not this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.30,0:31:06.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了证明他们还是错的\N{\fs90}To prove them wrong again,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.45,0:31:11.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,我决定前往这附近的切尔西训练场\N{\fs90}I decided to head for the nearby Chelsea training ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.43,0:31:14.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,这些才是懂车的人 不像你们两个\N{\fs90}These are people who understand cars, not like you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.78,0:31:17.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 他们懂车 所以他们才会买\N{\fs90}Yeah, they understand cars, that's why they buy
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.21,0:31:19.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,路虎和阿斯顿马丁\N{\fs90}Range Rovers and Aston Martins.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.31,0:31:20.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们会买这些\N{\fs90}They buy those things
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.87,0:31:22.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,是因为他们不知道还有这辆车\N{\fs90}cos they didn't know that you could do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.90,0:31:25.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我喜欢我的车 -它是坨屎\N{\fs90}- I like my car. - It's shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.65,0:31:33.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们会侧目的 不是吗\N{\fs90}They're flocking to it, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.09,0:31:34.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你就等着瞧 -你介意\N{\fs90}- You just watch. - Do you mind
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.92,0:31:37.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,我走开站在别人边上吗\N{\fs90}if I go and stand next to something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.32,0:31:40.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快一下球员来了\N{\fs90}Soon some players arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.47,0:31:42.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,给了理查德和船长一个机会\N{\fs90}which gave Richard and James a chance
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.60,0:31:45.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,来炫耀他们的足球知识\N{\fs90}to show off their footballing knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.33,0:31:47.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,你好高 你应该是个得分手\N{\fs90}You're really tall. You should play in goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.47,0:31:48.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 我是个得分手\N{\fs90}Yeah, I do, I play in goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.94,0:31:49.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我是个守门员  -我就知道\N{\fs90}- I'm the goalkeeper. - I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.97,0:31:51.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,你来自切尔西的哪个区\N{\fs90}What part of Chelsea are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.81,0:31:54.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我来自比利时 -噢\N{\fs90}- I'm from Belgium. - Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.04,0:31:57.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道他们是球员\N{\fs90}How do you know they're footballers?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.31,0:31:58.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 你们难道没有认出他们吗\N{\fs90}Well, do you not recognise them?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.43,0:32:01.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们穿着球衣\N{\fs90}They're in football outfits.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.21,0:32:02.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,他没有认出你\N{\fs90}He doesn't recognise you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.38,0:32:04.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,亚历克斯·弗格森 在哪里\N{\fs90}Where's... Where's Alex Ferguson?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.25,0:32:05.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么我们问他\N{\fs90}Why don't we ask him?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.35,0:32:09.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个时候我甩下了我无知的同事们\N{\fs90}At this point I dismissed my ignorant colleagues
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.72,0:32:12.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我可以自己操作字幕机\N{\fs90}so that I could operate the subtitle machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.03,0:32:27.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你会顶球吗 -可以\N{\fs90}- Can you do keepy-uppy? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.61,0:32:30.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,踢给我个球\N{\fs90}Take a shot at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.27,0:32:33.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,这太荒唐了 这个我能怎么办呢\N{\fs90}Well, that's ridiculous. What can I do with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.34,0:32:34.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,你应该跳起来\N{\fs90}You're supposed to jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.08,0:32:38.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得这个 可怕至极\N{\fs90}I think it is flipping horrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.95,0:32:41.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以你屠杀了一辆老爷车\N{\fs90}So you've butchered a classic car?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.79,0:32:44.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了 看这个 轻轻投掷\N{\fs90}Right, watch this. Little toss...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.34,0:32:47.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs90}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.38,0:32:49.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,你需要想一想\N{\fs90}You need to think of...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.01,0:33:06.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-哦 -拦住了\N{\fs90}- Ow. - Saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.65,0:33:15.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,在得出了\N{\fs90}Having established
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.32,0:33:17.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,所有顶级的职业球员都喜欢我的车之后\N{\fs90}that all top professional footballers loved my car,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.99,0:33:20.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们又重新上路了\N{\fs90}we got back on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.80,0:33:24.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,你拿到任何订单了吗\N{\fs90}Did you get any orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.23,0:33:25.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,我发下那个停车场\N{\fs90}I noticed that the car park
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.81,0:33:27.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,停满了奔驰G系\N{\fs90}was still full of Mercedes G-Class.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.40,0:33:29.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我看到了 -听着\N{\fs90}- I saw that. - Listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.27,0:33:32.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,我可以把它拿去拍卖\N{\fs90}I could put this into an auction,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.81,0:33:34.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,最奢侈的 最高档的那种\N{\fs90}one of those posh, up-market ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.76,0:33:36.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,它还是可以卖到12万英镑的\N{\fs90}and it would sell for £120,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.87,0:33:38.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,它不能\N{\fs90}It would not!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.44,0:33:41.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了再次证明他们是错的\N{\fs90}To prove them wrong again...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.03,0:33:58.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,先生们 人们在检查\N{\fs90}Gentlemen, people are examining...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.40,0:34:00.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 他们是主办方\N{\fs90}Yeah, they are the organisers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.40,0:34:02.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们在疑惑自己的地毯\N{\fs90}They're wondering about their carpet.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.20,0:34:07.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,由著名英国工作室手工打造\N{\fs90}"Handcrafted by a renowned British atelier...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.24,0:34:09.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,悲天悯人的融合经典与…\N{\fs90}sympathetically marries the chassis with..."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.28,0:34:14.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这个你写的 -当然是我写的\N{\fs90}- Did you write this? - Course I wrote it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.55,0:34:18.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,内饰有几个小地方需要注意\N{\fs90}"The interior would benefit from some minor attention."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.14,0:34:19.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好的 它可以 -加上一颗手榴弹\N{\fs90}- Well, it would. - With a hand grenade.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.87,0:34:21.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,批号132\N{\fs90}Lot number 132.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.74,0:34:23.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快拍卖就开始了\N{\fs90}Soon the auction was under way.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.72,0:34:28.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,法拉利308GTB 十一万八成交\N{\fs90}Ferrari 308 GTB, at £118,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.53,0:34:33.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,批号127 起价三十万\N{\fs90}Lot number 127, start me with this at 300,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.14,0:34:35.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,很多竞拍者都乐于\N{\fs90}And many of the punters were happy
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.10,0:34:38.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,为车拍出六位数\N{\fs90}to pay six-figure sums for the cars on offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.87,0:34:40.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,二十七万成交\N{\fs90}At 270,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.84,0:34:44.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,285 康塔什\N{\fs90}285 for the Countach.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.04,0:34:47.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,康塔什刚刚拍了285000英镑\N{\fs90}The Countach just went for £285,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.71,0:34:49.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我认为我可以把卓越\N{\fs90}I think I'm gonna sell The Excellent
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.90,0:34:51.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,卖出个更高的价钱\N{\fs90}for more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.08,0:34:53.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后时间到了\N{\fs90}And then it was time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.25,0:34:56.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,轮到了批号138A\N{\fs90}Moving on to lot number 138A.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.03,0:34:58.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,卓越\N{\fs90}The Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.92,0:35:00.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,它是一个绝妙的手工制作的\N{\fs90}It's a fantastic handcrafted,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.39,0:35:03.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常不平凡的机器  就像你看到的一样\N{\fs90}very unusual machine, as you can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.43,0:35:04.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不想让你…\N{\fs90}I don't want you...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.12,0:35:07.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,美丽又现代的梅赛德斯奔驰的车身\N{\fs90}Beautiful, stylish Mercedes Benz coachwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.76,0:35:10.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,-非常不寻常 独特 -不寻常\N{\fs90}- Very unusual, unique... - Unusual?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.80,0:35:12.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这个下午出售\N{\fs90}Here for sale this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.07,0:35:15.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,起拍价 如果你们愿意\N{\fs90}Start me if you will on this at...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.91,0:35:17.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,425英镑\N{\fs90}£425.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.94,0:35:20.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,在425英镑\N{\fs90}At £425...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.21,0:35:21.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,有出价超过400的吗\N{\fs90}Any advance at 400?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.98,0:35:23.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,500磅 550磅那里\N{\fs90}£500. 550 anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.90,0:35:26.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,-有人在出价 -600那里\N{\fs90}- Somebody's bid? - 600 here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.72,0:35:28.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,650 650 700现在\N{\fs90}650. 650. 700 now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.90,0:35:30.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们形式很俏\N{\fs90}We're rattling up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.49,0:35:33.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,700这里 700 800现在\N{\fs90}700 here. 700. 800 now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.86,0:35:35.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我们努力争取1000\N{\fs90}Let's go for 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.30,0:35:43.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我们继续  来啊 让我们卖了这辆车\N{\fs90}Let's get going. Come on, let's sell this car.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.76,0:35:48.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,-1000英镑在我的右边 -你在出价\N{\fs90}- £1,000 here on my right. - Are you bidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.01,0:35:51.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不 -杰里米 你在出价\N{\fs90}- No. - Jeremy, are you bidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.07,0:35:52.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,2000如果你希望\N{\fs90}2,000 if you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.12,0:35:54.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,两千五  二 五\N{\fs90}It's 2,000 and five. Two, five.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.38,0:35:57.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,三千现在 三千这里 三五有吗\N{\fs90}3,000 now. It's 3,000 here. Three, five anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.83,0:35:59.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,三 一\N{\fs90}Three, one.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.83,0:36:01.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,3100\N{\fs90}At 3,100.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.03,0:36:03.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,3200\N{\fs90}£3,200.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.01,0:36:05.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,3500\N{\fs90}At £3,500.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.74,0:36:08.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,-它花了我14000 -4000\N{\fs90}- It cost me 14,000. - 4,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.38,0:36:10.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,在4000\N{\fs90}At £4,000...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.36,0:36:12.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,在4000 还有更多的吗\N{\fs90}At £4,000, any more?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.04,0:36:18.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,在4000\N{\fs90}At £4,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.80,0:36:20.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,等下过来见我们\N{\fs90}Come and see us after.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.41,0:36:22.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,你失去了一万块\N{\fs90}You just lost ten grand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.31,0:36:24.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,他本可以把钱直接扔进厕所\N{\fs90}He could have just thrown it down the lavatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.94,0:36:38.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,它就是垃圾\N{\fs90}It was rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.06,0:36:40.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,等等\N{\fs90}Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.63,0:36:44.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,你在竞拍自己的车\N{\fs90}- You were bidding on your own car.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.63,0:36:47.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 只有一点点 我只是想让这势头继续\N{\fs90}Well, a bit. I just wanted to get the ball rolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.81,0:36:49.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是即使这样也没有用\N{\fs90}But even then it didn't work
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.07,0:36:50.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你只把它卖了四千块\N{\fs90}because you only sold it for four grand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.94,0:36:52.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,做这个花了你一万四英镑\N{\fs90}It cost you 14,000 to make
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.74,0:36:55.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以你花了我们出品公司一万英镑\N{\fs90}so you cost our production company £10,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.96,0:36:57.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,不不 这不对\N{\fs90}No, no, not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.76,0:37:00.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我订了保留价 -什么保留价\N{\fs90}- I put a reserve on it. - What reserve?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.18,0:37:02.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,十万英镑\N{\fs90}£100,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.22,0:37:04.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,-十万英镑 -所以它根本没有卖出去\N{\fs90}- £100,000? - So it didn't sell at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.98,0:37:07.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,也就是说你花了我们一万四千英镑\N{\fs90}which means you cost us £14,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.39,0:37:11.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 但是我们最后有了卓越\N{\fs90}Well, yes, but we've ended up with The Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.46,0:37:15.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 我们无法摆脱卓越了\N{\fs90}No, we're stuck with The Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.33,0:37:17.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,和你在一起工作 很难知道\N{\fs90}It's really difficult to know, working with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.90,0:37:19.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,像这样的事情 是雄心壮志\N{\fs90}things like this, is it ambition
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.97,0:37:22.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,还是你只是个疯子\N{\fs90}or are you a lunatic?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.74,0:37:25.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,难过的是现在并不是回答这个问题的时间\N{\fs90}Sadly there isn't time to answer that question,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.78,0:37:29.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为是时候进入我们的明星脑碰脑\N{\fs90}because it's time to play Celebrity Brain Crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.78,0:37:39.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们这周的嘉宾是一个当地的女孩\N{\fs90}Our guest this week is a local girl
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.67,0:37:44.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,为一首我历来最喜欢的流行歌\N{\fs90}who is responsible for one of my all-time favourite pop songs,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.09,0:37:46.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,99个红气球\N{\fs90}99 Red Balloons.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.47,0:37:48.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,她是一个歌手\N{\fs90}She is a singer,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.36,0:37:50.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,她是个腋毛爱好者\N{\fs90}she's an armpit hair enthusiast
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.67,0:37:53.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,她是个全能运动手\N{\fs90}and she's an all-round good sport.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.12,0:37:55.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们 让我们欢迎内娜\N{\fs90}Ladies and gentlemen, please welcome Nena!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.59,0:38:18.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,-她在哪里 -我不知道\N{\fs90}- Where is she? - I've got no idea. Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.26,0:38:22.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 哦 不\N{\fs90}Oh. Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.74,0:38:25.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,雾这么大很难看清\N{\fs90}It's hard to see through the smog,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.05,0:38:26.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是的 这是\N{\fs90}but yes, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.33,0:38:29.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,-哦不 -在那里发生的是\N{\fs90}- Oh, no. - What's happened here is...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.60,0:38:31.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,内娜\N{\fs90}Nena...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.34,0:38:33.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 她被99只\N{\fs90}yes, she's been carried away by 99...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.16,0:38:38.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,-红气球给带走  -哦不\N{\fs90}- ...red balloons. - Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.28,0:38:39.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,真坏\N{\fs90}Bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.82,0:38:47.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,那就是说她不会来了 然后呢\N{\fs90}Does that mean she's not coming on, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.29,0:38:50.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,穿着 她已经飘到平流层了\N{\fs90}Well, James, she's floated up into the stratosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.10,0:38:53.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,她的眼皮被冻掉了而且她的肺也翻出来了\N{\fs90}her eyelids have frozen over and her lungs are inside out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.32,0:38:54.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以那是一个不\N{\fs90}So that is a no.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.50,0:38:56.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过 没关系\N{\fs90}It's OK, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.98,0:38:59.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们早就料到内娜会飘走\N{\fs90}We anticipated that Nena may float away.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.72,0:39:02.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们有一个备用计划 让我们激活这个 你们坐坐好\N{\fs90}We have a back-up plan. We'll activate it. You sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.70,0:39:06.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看 事情是这样的 越来越多的东西\N{\fs90}You see, the thing is... that more and more stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.36,0:39:09.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,这些日子里 靠充电电池驱动\N{\fs90}these days, is being powered by rechargeable batteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.65,0:39:11.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,你知道的 手机 笔记本 那种东西\N{\fs90}You know, phones, laptops. That sort of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.56,0:39:13.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个给世界带来了一个问题\N{\fs90}And this is giving the world a bit of a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.85,0:39:17.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为在英国 我们的电力公司只生产\N{\fs90}Because in Britain, our power companies only produce
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.87,0:39:21.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,比我们所需的多5%的电力\N{\fs90}five per cent more power than we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.67,0:39:23.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们勉强度日\N{\fs90}We're only just coping.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.56,0:39:26.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,在美国这情况更糟糕\N{\fs90}It's actually worse in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.36,0:39:29.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为他们生产的比他们实际所需少16%\N{\fs90}cos they produce 16% less than they actually need,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.76,0:39:32.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就意味着他们要进口电力\N{\fs90}which means they have to import electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.33,0:39:34.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以当越来越多的人开始\N{\fs90}So what is gonna happen as more and more people
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.90,0:39:37.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,购买和使用电动汽车 会发生什么呢\N{\fs90}are buying and using electric cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.47,0:39:39.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们会需要更多的电力 我们可能没办法应对\N{\fs90}We're gonna need more power. We may not be able to cope.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.92,0:39:41.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,解决方法 你可能会想\N{\fs90}The solution, you may think,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.57,0:39:43.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,多建几个发电厂\N{\fs90}is to build more power stations.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.38,0:39:45.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,但即使你仅仅只是这样建议\N{\fs90}But if you even suggest that,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.18,0:39:47.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,怪胡子的环保主义者就会东奔西跑\N{\fs90}weird-beard environmentalists run around
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.27,0:39:48.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,挥着他们的手臂 说\N{\fs90}waving their arms in the air, going,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.63,0:39:50.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,那北极熊和蝙蝠还有蝾螈怎么办\N{\fs90}"What about the polar bear and the bats and the newt?"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.81,0:39:53.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管怎样 重点是我们需要更多更多的能源\N{\fs90}Anyway, the point is we are going to need more and more power
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.67,0:39:56.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,来为我们手机 笔记本和车里的电池充电\N{\fs90}to charge the batteries in our phones, laptops and cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.67,0:40:00.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们要从哪里得到呢 -所以这让我们开始思考\N{\fs90}- Where are we gonna get it from? - This got us thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.10,0:40:03.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们一天可以产生多少电力\N{\fs90}How much electricity could we possibly generate every day
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.78,0:40:05.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,仅仅在我们的日常生活中\N{\fs90}just during our normal lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.43,0:40:08.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在某些程度上可以利用它\N{\fs90}And what if we could harness it in some way?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.10,0:40:14.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里是一座位于伦敦中心的办公大楼\N{\fs90}This is an office block in the centre of London.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.61,0:40:18.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,和很多办公大楼一样 它有旋转门\N{\fs90}Like many office blocks, it has a revolving door,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.18,0:40:22.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,随着人来人往一直旋转\N{\fs90}which spins constantly as people come and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.28,0:40:27.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以说 为什么不把门变成一个发电机呢\N{\fs90}So, why not simply connect that door to a generator
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.16,0:40:31.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,把旋转的动能变成电能\N{\fs90}and turn all that spinning into electricity?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.96,0:40:34.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然 并不只有旋转门\N{\fs90}And it's not just revolving doors, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.83,0:40:38.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们很多人都有狗狗\N{\fs90}Many of us have dogs
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.72,0:40:41.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,每天我们遛狗的时候\N{\fs90}and every day we take those dogs for a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.67,0:40:46.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,狗狗蹦蹦跳跳四处乱窜\N{\fs90}A dog scampers hither and thither, running ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.83,0:40:47.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,在灌木丛下嗅来嗅去\N{\fs90}and snouting under hedgerows.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.98,0:40:52.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以说为什么不给狗狗安一个这样的拖车\N{\fs90}So why not attach it to a trailer like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.45,0:40:53.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,狗狗把小车一路拖着\N{\fs90}Dog pulls the trailer along.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.05,0:40:56.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这里轮子里是一个发电机\N{\fs90}Inside this wheel is a dynamo.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.70,0:40:59.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,它发的电 通过这些电线\N{\fs90}It makes electricity, goes along these wires
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.12,0:41:00.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,流进这个电容\N{\fs90}and into this capacitor,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.43,0:41:02.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,当这个仪表读数达到百分之百的时候\N{\fs90}and when that dial reads 100%,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.14,0:41:04.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的手机就充上电了\N{\fs90}I'm charging my phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.22,0:41:05.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看 狗狗被套上了\N{\fs90}So, dog's harnessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.59,0:41:07.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,这很简单 装上拖车\N{\fs90}That was easy. Attached to the trailer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.98,0:41:10.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要做的就是让她走起来\N{\fs90}All I've got to do is set her going.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.33,0:41:13.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且我都计划好了 看\N{\fs90}And I've even planned for that. So, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.17,0:41:14.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,接\N{\fs90}Fetch!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.47,0:41:19.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,啊哈\N{\fs90}Ah-haa!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.10,0:41:20.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,你最喜欢这个了\N{\fs90}Yeah! Your favourite!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.31,0:41:25.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,追\N{\fs90}Chase!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.35,0:41:28.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,这狗狗是不是坏掉了\N{\fs90}Maybe this dog's broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.85,0:41:32.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,与此同时 在伦敦\N{\fs90}Meanwhile, back in London,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.28,0:41:33.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯通过一个连接在\N{\fs90}James was charging his phone
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.05,0:41:36.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,旋转门上的玩意儿给他的手机充电\N{\fs90}from a contraption he'd fitted to the revolving door.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.17,0:41:51.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,就连杰里米也想采取行动\N{\fs90}And even Jeremy had decided to get in on the action.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.84,0:41:55.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,学校的运动节\N{\fs90}This school sports day,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.74,0:41:58.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我的脑海里 这可是个发电厂啊\N{\fs90}in my mind, is a power station.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.11,0:42:01.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们要做的 只是给这些孩子们绑上挽具\N{\fs90}All we have to do is fit the children with harnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.27,0:42:04.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,用不了多久这个就会被充满了\N{\fs90}and I could have this charged up in no time at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.75,0:42:08.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,开始吧\N{\fs90}Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.02,0:42:10.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,效果立竿见影\N{\fs90}Straightaway we can see
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.10,0:42:13.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,电流已经出现了\N{\fs90}that charge is being produced.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.38,0:42:14.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是很多 但还是有一点的\N{\fs90}Not much, but some.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.43,0:42:17.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,加油啊 你们加油啊\N{\fs90}Come on, all of you! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.80,0:42:21.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,用上后背的力量 快赶上他 加油\N{\fs90}Put your back into it! Catch him! Chop-chop!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.67,0:42:25.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,这主意简直是神来之笔\N{\fs90}This is the work of a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.71,0:42:27.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,回到乡下\N{\fs90}Back in the countryside,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.24,0:42:28.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,我修理好了我的狗\N{\fs90}I'd mended my dog
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.81,0:42:31.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,事情在这里也进展的不错\N{\fs90}and things were going well here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.38,0:42:34.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,正如你所见 狗狗正在跑步\N{\fs90}As you can see, the dog is now running,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.35,0:42:35.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,轮子也在旋转\N{\fs90}the wheels are turning,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.65,0:42:37.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,电力正在源源不断的产生\N{\fs90}electricity is being generated.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.52,0:42:40.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,他简直就是个四条腿的塞拉菲尔德核电厂嘛\N{\fs90}He's basically a four-legged Sellafield!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.99,0:42:44.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,难过的是 在伦敦 那是中午\N{\fs90}Sadly, however, in London, it was the middle of the day
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.76,0:42:47.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,没人用詹姆斯的旋转门\N{\fs90}and no one had been using James's door.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.93,0:42:52.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,因此 他的手机快没电了\N{\fs90}As a result, his phone was dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.53,0:42:54.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,他不得已采取了非常手段\N{\fs90}So he had to get radical.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.11,0:43:10.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,15%.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.88,0:43:12.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,真棒\N{\fs90}Nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.99,0:43:16.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,除了一点点小问题\N{\fs90}Apart from a couple of hiccups...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.12,0:43:17.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,走你\N{\fs90}Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.96,0:43:24.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,你得再努点力啊\N{\fs90}You'll have to put a little bit more effort in than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.56,0:43:26.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,一切进行的都不错\N{\fs90}...everything was going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.87,0:43:28.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,电力源源不断\N{\fs90}The power was flooding in.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.03,0:43:30.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,好棒\N{\fs90}Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.47,0:43:32.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,25%.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.67,0:43:34.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们不得不承认\N{\fs90}And we were forced to conclude
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.98,0:43:37.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,今天对于我们来说都是成功之日\N{\fs90}that it had been a successful day for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.61,0:43:40.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,额 当说出所有人的时候\N{\fs90}Well, when I say all of us...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.58,0:43:42.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,那个 你听我说\N{\fs90}No. Look, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.88,0:43:46.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,我知道你为什么在这里\N{\fs90}I can see why you're here. Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.85,0:43:49.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,很明显 给孩子们绑上挽具\N{\fs90}Obviously, fitting children with harnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.76,0:43:52.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后拍摄他们\N{\fs90}and then videoing them,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.23,0:43:53.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们还不是我的孩子\N{\fs90}and they're not my children...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.77,0:44:07.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,我给我的手机冲了45%的电\N{\fs90}I got... I got 45% charge in my phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.18,0:44:08.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,我冲了41%\N{\fs90}I got 41% charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.67,0:44:12.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,我受到了另外一种电\N{\fs90}I got a different sort of charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.88,0:44:14.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管怎样 自从我们已经证明了\N{\fs90}Anyway, since we had proved...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.63,0:44:15.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 其实是哈蒙德和我已经证明了\N{\fs90}well, Hammond and I had proved...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.92,0:44:18.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,可以这样给手机充电\N{\fs90}that it was possible to charge up a telephone...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.72,0:44:21.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,我开始好奇 我们能不能给车充电\N{\fs90}I began to wonder if we could charge up a car
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.99,0:44:25.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,用一些几乎没有价值的东西\N{\fs90}using nothing more than vanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.16,0:44:31.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,在伦敦 有超过750家健身房\N{\fs90}In London alone, there are over 750 gyms,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.25,0:44:33.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,每天里面都是人\N{\fs90}and every day they are full of people
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.43,0:44:36.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,把东西提起来再放下去\N{\fs90}picking things up and putting them down again
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.10,0:44:38.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以他们可以更有吸引力\N{\fs90}so they can be more attractive.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.24,0:44:42.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以说 为什么不利用一下这巨大的能量\N{\fs90}So why not use all this colossal effort?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.64,0:44:45.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我们利用它吧\N{\fs90}Let's harness it!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.81,0:44:49.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们就是这么做的\N{\fs90}And that's exactly what we have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.36,0:44:51.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,健身房里的10台机器\N{\fs90}Ten of the machines in this gym
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.36,0:44:52.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,都连接上了一个装置\N{\fs90}have been connected to a device
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.78,0:44:55.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,可以产生平稳的电流\N{\fs90}which produces a smooth flow of electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.50,0:44:59.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,再输送到停车场里的G-Wiz上\N{\fs90}that's sent outside to this G-Wiz in the car park.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.23,0:45:03.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 电池里一点电都没有\N{\fs90}Right now the battery is flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.05,0:45:05.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,我把这个插销插上\N{\fs90}So I'm going to plug it in
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.67,0:45:08.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,8个小时之后 我们看看健身房里产生的电\N{\fs90}and then after eight hours, we'll see how far I can drive
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.27,0:45:11.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,能让我们能把车开多远\N{\fs90}on electricity that's been generated in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.63,0:45:27.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,加油啊 你在偷懒呢\N{\fs90}Come on, you're slacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.30,0:45:45.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,好啦 从健身房断开连接\N{\fs90}Right. Unplug from the gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.71,0:45:49.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看我们能走多远吧\N{\fs90}Let's see how far we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.28,0:46:00.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,看啊 此刻犹如史诗般 因为我开着\N{\fs90}Look at this. This is epic because I'm driving along
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.23,0:46:02.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,一台车 算是吧\N{\fs90}in a car, sort of.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.79,0:46:04.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有燃料被燃烧\N{\fs90}No fossil fuel has been burned,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.46,0:46:06.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有原子被裂变\N{\fs90}and no atoms have been split.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.18,0:46:08.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有什么被压裂\N{\fs90}Nothing's been fracked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.74,0:46:18.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,看哪 那里有人在推着婴儿车\N{\fs90}Look, there's a man pushing that pushchair.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.80,0:46:20.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,在上面装个小发电机\N{\fs90}Stick a little dynamo on that,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.01,0:46:24.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,孩子得到了一些新鲜空气 我则充到了更多电\N{\fs90}kid gets some fresh air, I get more battery charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.31,0:46:31.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,这样子的安排是共赢之举\N{\fs90}It's difficult to see who loses from this arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.76,0:46:34.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我得以回家 基本上什么也没消耗\N{\fs90}I get a trip home, effectively for nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.59,0:46:37.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,那些去健身房的人们感觉好 看着也好\N{\fs90}the people going to the gym feel good, look good,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.79,0:46:40.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们变得健康 NHS省了钱\N{\fs90}they become healthier, the NHS saves money,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.03,0:46:41.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为人们会更加少的\N{\fs90}cos people are less likely
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.86,0:46:43.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,中风 你有没有\N{\fs90}to have strokes and what have you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.60,0:46:46.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果一百个人里有一个得到了免费的健…\N{\fs90}If one person in a hundred gets a free gy...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.47,0:46:52.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,等等\N{\fs90}Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.68,0:46:59.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,我正在享受用踏板驾驶\N{\fs90}I was enjoying driving on pedal
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.32,0:47:01.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后用交叉训练器发电\N{\fs90}and cross-trainer power!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.18,0:47:07.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,随着这个 我觉得是时候回帐篷了\N{\fs90}And with that, I think it's back to the tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.59,0:47:15.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 詹姆斯梅\N{\fs90}James... James May,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.83,0:47:18.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,你开了多远\N{\fs90}how far did you get
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.86,0:47:21.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,在充了8小时电以后\N{\fs90}after eight hours of charging?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.27,0:47:23.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,实际上 比我预期的好\N{\fs90}Actually, it was better than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.80,0:47:25.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,我开了34公里\N{\fs90}I did 21 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.70,0:47:28.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,等等 从我们在伦敦的办公室\N{\fs90}Hang on, though. To get from our office in London
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.84,0:47:30.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,到在威尔士边上额我的家\N{\fs90}to my home in nearly Wales,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.81,0:47:33.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是209公里 以34公里\N{\fs90}that's 130 miles, 21 miles at...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.98,0:47:36.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以要在健身房停六次 每次八小时\N{\fs90}So six stops at gyms, eight hours a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.32,0:47:37.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,而实际驾驶\N{\fs90}and the actual driving,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.48,0:47:39.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,会花去我三天\N{\fs90}it would take me three days
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.36,0:47:40.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,才能到家\N{\fs90}to get home!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.72,0:47:43.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者 哈蒙德 只是一个想法\N{\fs90}Or, Hammond, just an idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.09,0:47:45.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,你可以买一辆汽油驱动的车\N{\fs90}you could maybe get a petrol-powered car,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.96,0:47:47.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,在里面加点汽油\N{\fs90}put some petrol in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.85,0:47:49.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,在两个小时里到家\N{\fs90}and be home in two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.78,0:47:51.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,这更好 我要这么做\N{\fs90}That's a better... I'm gonna do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.43,0:47:52.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 所以瞧\N{\fs90}Yes. So there we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.72,0:47:54.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,那就是未来 石油铸成的\N{\fs90}That's the future, and it's made of petrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.03,0:47:57.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们就这么愉快的决定了\N{\fs90}So we've addressed that nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.94,0:48:01.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,继续节目\N{\fs90}Moving on...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.28,0:48:06.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在\N{\fs90}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.75,0:48:09.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,世界各地的人们\N{\fs90}There are people all over the world
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.05,0:48:12.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,认为我们永久地处在核战争\N{\fs90}who believe we are permanently on the verge of nuclear war,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.83,0:48:15.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,外星人入侵和僵尸危机的边缘\N{\fs90}alien invasion or zombie attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.59,0:48:17.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不是一个少数人的事\N{\fs90}It isn't a niche thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.27,0:48:19.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,有至少十二万的人\N{\fs90}There's 120,000 of these people at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.63,0:48:21.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,称自己末日族\N{\fs90}They call themselves preppers.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.73,0:48:23.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,-蠢货 闭嘴\N{\fs90}- Morons. - Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.40,0:48:25.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,-白痴 -而且这些末日族们\N{\fs90}- Idiots. - And these preppers,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.70,0:48:28.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了应对灭绝性事件\N{\fs90}in order to prepare for an extinction-level event,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.33,0:48:30.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,在家里囤积必需用品\N{\fs90}stock their homes with essential supplies,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.45,0:48:32.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们去森林里练习战术\N{\fs90}they go out into the woods and practise tactics,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.20,0:48:35.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们还创造了他们口中的跑路神器\N{\fs90}and they create what they call bug-out cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.98,0:48:37.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,那简直太有才了 这里有一辆 看\N{\fs90}They're brilliant. Here is one. Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.34,0:48:39.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,-看它 -是的我知道\N{\fs90}- Look at that! - Yeah! I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.54,0:48:42.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不 哈蒙德 这个不有才 -它就是\N{\fs90}- No, Hammond, that is not brilliant. - It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.48,0:48:45.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,你是在所我们可以将一些钉子放在现代的轮子里\N{\fs90}Are you saying we can prepare for a nuclear attack
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.62,0:48:49.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,来预防核攻击\N{\fs90}by putting some spikes on the wheels of a Hyundai?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.72,0:48:52.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果核攻击\N{\fs90}What if the nuclear attack
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.23,0:48:53.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,来自现代的背后呢\N{\fs90}comes from the back of the Hyundai?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.01,0:48:56.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,你能对这辆车做的只有\N{\fs90}All you're gonna do with that car
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.18,0:48:59.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,-拿它来跑酷 -哦不要这么消极\N{\fs90}- is snag your jumper on it. - Oh, don't be so negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.12,0:49:02.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,在节目里你可是浪费了我们一万四千英镑\N{\fs90}In this show you have wasted 14,000 of our pounds
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.34,0:49:03.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,在你那愚蠢的奔驰车上\N{\fs90}on your stupid Mercedes car.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.87,0:49:05.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,你浪费了我们所有的时间\N{\fs90}You have wasted all of our time
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.67,0:49:07.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,在你那辆汗水驱动的电动车上\N{\fs90}with your sweat-powered electric car.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.34,0:49:10.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我的事  让我就这么干\N{\fs90}This is my thing. Let me do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.36,0:49:12.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,你有没有认识到没有\N{\fs90}You do realise there's no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.58,0:49:13.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,像僵尸这种东西存在 对吗\N{\fs90}as a zombie, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.67,0:49:16.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,不要给他戳穿了\N{\fs90}Don't spoil it for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.08,0:49:18.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,我喜欢变成末日族这个概念\N{\fs90}I like the idea of being a prepper,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.03,0:49:22.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我觉得我要尝试做我自己的跑路神器\N{\fs90}so I thought I'd have a go at making my own bug-out car.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.19,0:49:32.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是我的作品\N{\fs90}This is what I came up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.93,0:49:39.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,它原是一辆大众面包车 高顶版\N{\fs90}It started life as a VW campervan, high-top version.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.57,0:49:42.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我除去了它的嬉皮传统\N{\fs90}But I've stripped it of its hippie heritage
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.81,0:49:45.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,把它变成了一辆敢于在危险的\N{\fs90}to turn it into a vehicle that can bare its teeth
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.54,0:49:48.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,末日世界中 露出它的尖牙的车\N{\fs90}in a dangerous, post-apocalyptic world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.48,0:49:53.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且 我很喜欢它\N{\fs90}And I love it!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.22,0:49:58.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,我对这辆车不能更满意了\N{\fs90}I'm so unbelievably pleased with this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.01,0:50:04.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得自己无可匹敌 准备就绪\N{\fs90}I feel invincible, ready, prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.66,0:50:06.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,考虑到我所做的改装\N{\fs90}Which is hardly surprising,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.78,0:50:09.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不足为奇\N{\fs90}given the modifications I've made.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.17,0:50:12.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,在前面 一个破城槌\N{\fs90}At the front, a battering ram.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.27,0:50:14.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你很明确路上不会太平\N{\fs90}You can be pretty sure the roads won't be clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.87,0:50:16.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,这些槌靠钉子钉劳\N{\fs90}The ram itself is fitted with spikes
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.91,0:50:19.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了在近距离抵挡僵尸\N{\fs90}for fending off zombies at close quarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.27,0:50:20.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后 在最顶上\N{\fs90}Then, up top,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.11,0:50:22.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,一组强大的聚光灯\N{\fs90}a bank of powerful rally lights
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.30,0:50:25.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,用来穿透核冬天的黑暗\N{\fs90}to cut through the murky soup of a nuclear winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.62,0:50:28.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然 不是每个我见到的人都会友好\N{\fs90}Of course, not everyone I meet will be friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.72,0:50:30.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以在这里\N{\fs90}So, up here...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.83,0:50:38.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,武器库\N{\fs90}...weapons rack.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.10,0:50:39.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,所有我需要的\N{\fs90}Everything I need
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.40,0:50:42.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我对抗食人族和僵尸时自卫的东西\N{\fs90}to defend myself against cannibals and zombies.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.80,0:50:45.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个转角 水 必需之物\N{\fs90}Round here, water. Essential.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.74,0:50:48.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有一些微妙的事物 我可不想太引人注目\N{\fs90}Subtle stuff too. I don't want to stand out,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.44,0:50:50.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以这是伪装漆\N{\fs90}hence the camouflage paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.36,0:50:51.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,但可能是最重要的\N{\fs90}But perhaps most importantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.94,0:50:53.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的整辆逃跑露营车\N{\fs90}the whole of my bug-out campervan
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.71,0:50:55.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,都武装了装甲\N{\fs90}has been armour-plated.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.08,0:50:58.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,我真的什么都想到了\N{\fs90}I really have thought of everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.72,0:50:59.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,不你没有\N{\fs90}No, you haven't!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.99,0:51:02.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,你所做的就是毁了一辆完好的露营车\N{\fs90}All you've done is ruined a perfectly good campervan.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.56,0:51:04.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 我才没有 这很有才\N{\fs90}No, I haven't! It's brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.70,0:51:06.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,它周身都是防弹的\N{\fs90}It's bullet-proof all over!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.23,0:51:08.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,-防弹的 是吗 -是的\N{\fs90}- Bullet-proof? Is it? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.23,0:51:09.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是吗 -是的\N{\fs90}- Is it? - Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.83,0:51:12.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,-哦听上去像是 -坦克般的感觉\N{\fs90}- Oh, yeah, sounds like it. - Tanks feel like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.33,0:51:15.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 这些枪 用它们\N{\fs90}OK, then, these are guns. Use them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.57,0:51:18.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,-什么 朝你 -不 朝车 射它\N{\fs90}- What, on you? - No, on the van. Shoot it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.74,0:51:20.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们准备好了嘛先生们 -好了\N{\fs90}- Are we ready, gentlemen? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.81,0:51:24.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈 没有穿透\N{\fs90}Ha! Didn't go through!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.18,0:51:25.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,只削下了块漆 你也只能做到这样了\N{\fs90}Just chipped the paint. That's all you've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.98,0:51:27.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的 哈蒙德 -怎么\N{\fs90}- Yes. Hammond? - Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.83,0:51:29.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,你所表达的是这些外星人\N{\fs90}What you're suggesting is these aliens,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.58,0:51:31.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们旅行了数万亿英里\N{\fs90}they're going to travel trillions of miles
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.05,0:51:35.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,用一个我们想都不敢想的推进系统\N{\fs90}using a propulsion system that we can't even conceive
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.29,0:51:38.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后他们试图控制这个世界\N{\fs90}and then they're going to try and take over the world
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.09,0:51:40.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,用177步枪\N{\fs90}using .177 air rifles?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.33,0:51:42.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧如果他们这样 我应该准备好了\N{\fs90}Well, if they do, I shall be ready for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.13,0:51:48.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,特别考虑到我在这里所做的一切\N{\fs90}Especially given what I've done in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.54,0:51:51.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,在内部 我把这个曾经简陋的露营车\N{\fs90}Inside, I've turned this once-humble campervan
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.01,0:51:55.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,变成了可以想象到的最高科技控制中心\N{\fs90}into literally the highest-tech command centre imaginable.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.87,0:51:58.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,在前面 二氧化碳洗涤塔\N{\fs90}Up front, carbon dioxide scrubbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.34,0:51:59.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像在阿波罗13上的那个\N{\fs90}just like the ones on Apollo 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.85,0:52:03.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们可以净化空气 甚至辐射\N{\fs90}They will purify the air, even in case of radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.38,0:52:07.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且你可以测量辐射 在这里的这个机器上\N{\fs90}And you can measure that radiation on these systems up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.79,0:52:10.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,水 你可能找不到它\N{\fs90}Water. You may not be able to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.26,0:52:12.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,需要制造水 这很必须\N{\fs90}Need to make it. It's essential.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.36,0:52:15.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,我安装了一个系统可以回收尿液\N{\fs90}I've fitted a system that recycles urine.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.53,0:52:18.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,基本上你在那里小号\N{\fs90}Basically you do your number ones up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.10,0:52:21.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,操作泵\N{\fs90}Operate the pumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.20,0:52:22.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们将结果输送上去\N{\fs90}They send the results up,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.63,0:52:25.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,进入净水系统\N{\fs90}across, and into the water purification system.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.74,0:52:30.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,那里浮现的就会使最纯净的饮用水\N{\fs90}It emerges from that as purest drinking water.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.65,0:52:37.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,食物 我会需要的 我有一只鸡\N{\fs90}Food. I'm gonna need it. I've got a chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.52,0:52:39.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,它下单 它们滚到那里\N{\fs90}It lays eggs. They go in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.82,0:52:42.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且可能是最好的 鹅肝酱\N{\fs90}And perhaps best of all, the pâté de foie gras
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.02,0:52:44.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,在逃跑神器小社区\N{\fs90}of the bug-out community...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.56,0:52:46.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,鸡汤\N{\fs90}chicken soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.66,0:52:49.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这一切 启程去往荒野\N{\fs90}I love all this. Setting out into the wilderness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.65,0:52:51.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,用我这装了轮子的小小房子\N{\fs90}in my little house on wheels,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.60,0:52:56.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,知道无论发生什么 我都有所有需要的东西\N{\fs90}knowing I've got everything I need, whatever happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.14,0:52:58.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么鬼\N{\fs90}What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.14,0:53:03.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,我穿透了它的防弹装甲了吗\N{\fs90}Am I penetrating his bulletproof armour?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.14,0:53:06.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 还有他的吃的\N{\fs90}Yes. And his food.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.85,0:53:10.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 那是我的尿\N{\fs90}Oh! That's my own urine!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.22,0:53:15.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是你们两个做的吗 -是的就是他\N{\fs90}- Are you two doing this? - Yes, he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.15,0:53:18.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我是你我就会让开\N{\fs90}I'd get out of the way if I were you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.52,0:53:20.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,那只鸡的问题是它老是动\N{\fs90}The trouble with the chicken is, it moves around,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.85,0:53:22.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,让这个变的有点…\N{\fs90}making this a...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.16,0:53:26.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,-哦好主意 -难道不是吗\N{\fs90}- Oh, good idea! - Isn't it!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.97,0:53:31.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 装弹中 船长  装弹中\N{\fs90}Right, reloading, James. Reloading.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.78,0:53:33.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦好的\N{\fs90}Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.05,0:53:47.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好枪法 -还不坏 不是吗\N{\fs90}- Good shot. - Not bad, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.52,0:53:50.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,胜负已经定了 真的\N{\fs90}Sort of game over now, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.82,0:53:51.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\fs90}Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.23,0:53:54.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\fs90}Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.53,0:53:59.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,其实游戏还没结束呢\N{\fs90}It wasn't game over, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.40,0:54:01.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我又回到工作台前\N{\fs90}because I went back to the drawing board
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.33,0:54:03.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,开始干活了\N{\fs90}and started again.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.00,0:54:08.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,三个月努力的成果\N{\fs90}Three months' work.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.37,0:54:10.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我还是延用了一样的内饰设计\N{\fs90}I've used the same basic interior set-up,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.64,0:54:13.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过我完全重构了装甲镀层\N{\fs90}but I've completely re-thought the armour plating,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.35,0:54:15.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以说无论他俩上什么家伙\N{\fs90}so that whatever those two have...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.56,0:54:26.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 弯刀轻型侦查坦克登场\N{\fs90}Now, this is a Scimitar light reconnaissance tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.86,0:54:31.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,该坦克型号小速度快 而且机动性强\N{\fs90}It's small, it's quite fast, and it's quite manoeuvrable.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.76,0:54:34.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的职责就是像山羊一样环游整个战场\N{\fs90}Its job is to skip around the battlefield like a goat
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.30,0:54:36.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且找到目标\N{\fs90}and find stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.44,0:54:43.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看哈蒙德 惊慌失措的疯狂逃命\N{\fs90}Now, look at Hammond, running around in a mad panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.24,0:54:45.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,他觉得我要打他 但是我并不会\N{\fs90}He thinks I'm gonna shoot him, but I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.84,0:54:49.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,我只在这用激光来给他定位\N{\fs90}I'm just here to mark him with a laser.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.48,0:54:51.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,他才是开火的那位\N{\fs90}He's gonna shoot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.39,0:55:02.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 这是辆挑战者2型主战坦克\N{\fs90}Yes, this is a Challenger 2 main battle tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.73,0:55:05.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且这绝对是一辆跑路神器\N{\fs90}And this really is a bug-out vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.93,0:55:08.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,它绝对要比 我也不了解\N{\fs90}It's certainly a lot better than, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.27,0:55:11.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,轮子上有尖刺的现代要厉害很多\N{\fs90}a Hyundai with spikes on the wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.47,0:55:15.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,它能够保护它的雇主们防御\N{\fs90}It'll totally protect its occupants from radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.31,0:55:17.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,辐射 核放射性沉降 毒气\N{\fs90}nuclear fallout, gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.68,0:55:21.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,由于它强大的护甲 甚至还能防御住任何\N{\fs90}even a direct hit, thanks to its incredible armour,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.28,0:55:23.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,战场武器的迎面一击\N{\fs90}from any known battlefield weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.85,0:55:27.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后这个就是大炮了\N{\fs90}Then there's this gun, which is...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.55,0:55:30.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,没什么别的可以形容它了 巨大无比\N{\fs90}there's no other word... enormous!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.66,0:55:31.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,120毫米口径\N{\fs90}120mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.02,0:55:33.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且它能击中任何目标\N{\fs90}And it could hit a target...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.69,0:55:37.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,就拿理查德哈蒙德的面包车来说\N{\fs90}let's say Richard Hammond's van...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.10,0:55:41.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,期间还保持着48KM/H的速度在颠簸路面上行驶\N{\fs90}while the tank itself is doing 30mph over rough ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.87,0:55:46.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而 今天我打算静止的时候开火\N{\fs90}I think, though, today I shall fire while stationary
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.34,0:55:48.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我想好好品味一下这个瞬间\N{\fs90}because I want to savour the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.91,0:55:51.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 谢啦 兄弟们 我们就停这吧\N{\fs90}OK, thank you, chaps. If we could stop there...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.84,0:55:53.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 到驾驶席去\N{\fs90}Right, going down.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.14,0:55:54.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,收到 去驾驶席\N{\fs90}Roger. Going down.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.15,0:55:59.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,哎呦我操\N{\fs90}Oh, dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.69,0:56:05.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,我装了一发高爆弹\N{\fs90}I've loaded the gun with a high-explosive shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.42,0:56:06.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是个曳光弹 所以我们能\N{\fs90}It's a tracer shell, so we'll be able
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.06,0:56:08.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,在炮弹击中目标的时候\N{\fs90}to monitor its progress
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.56,0:56:11.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,看到它的轨迹\N{\fs90}as it arcs toward the target.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.53,0:56:13.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,克拉克森指挥官 这想法棒极了\N{\fs90}Oh, Commander Clarkson, this is fantastic!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.73,0:56:16.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能从这里看见他 你找到他了吗\N{\fs90}I can see him right there. Have you got him?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.10,0:56:17.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fs90}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.17,0:56:20.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,一群混蛋\N{\fs90}You bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.47,0:56:22.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,直接让他从痛苦中解脱出来吧 好不好\N{\fs90}Oh, just put him out of his misery, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.91,0:56:24.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,开火\N{\fs90}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.89,0:56:43.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不太确信他的跑路工具\N{\fs90}I'm not sure his bug-out vehicle was quite as strong
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.73,0:56:45.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,能像他让你们深信不疑的那样坚固\N{\fs90}as he may have led you to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.37,0:56:51.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\fs90}Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.58,0:57:03.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,好几个月以后\N{\fs90}Many months later,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.08,0:57:05.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我已经准备好发布我第三次尝试\N{\fs90}I was ready to unveil my third attempt...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.15,0:57:09.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,一辆固若金汤的堡垒\N{\fs90}...an impregnable fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.96,0:57:17.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,这才是跑路天堂\N{\fs90}This is bug-out heaven!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.06,0:57:21.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,我可用尽了我的灵感\N{\fs90}I've used as my inspiration
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.60,0:57:23.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,装甲可是外星科技\N{\fs90}the armoured personnel carrier from Aliens,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.94,0:57:27.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,照理来讲能把西格妮韦弗\N{\fs90}on the basis that if it can protect Sigourney Weaver
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.77,0:57:30.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,武装到牙齿\N{\fs90}from that metal bitey thing with teeth,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.04,0:57:35.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,它能保护我防御杰里米和詹姆斯的攻击\N{\fs90}it can keep me safe from Jeremy Clarkson and James May.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.08,0:57:38.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车以Alvis Stalwart军卡为基础\N{\fs90}Underneath this beast are the basic elements of an Alvis Stalwart.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.88,0:57:42.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以已经有装甲 还水陆两栖\N{\fs90}So it was already armour-plated, amphibious,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.32,0:57:43.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,动力巨大\N{\fs90}massively powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.76,0:57:45.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,六轮驱动 四轮转向\N{\fs90}six-wheel drive and four-wheel steering.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.10,0:57:55.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我所作的 就是改进它\N{\fs90}And what I've gone and done is improve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.71,0:58:07.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,它有蜂巢结构的\N{\fs90}It's got a honeycombed lattice work
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.25,0:58:09.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,钢陶装甲\N{\fs90}of ceramic-steel armour plating.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.45,0:58:11.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,比你能在A1M1坦克上找到的装甲\N{\fs90}It's three times thicker than the armour you'll find
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.75,0:58:15.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,还要厚3倍\N{\fs90}on the turret of an Abrams A1M1 tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.99,0:58:23.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了测试 我对外壳打了发7.62毫米的\N{\fs90}In testing, I fired a 7.62 round at that hull,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.93,0:58:26.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,而它只留下这么一个印子\N{\fs90}and all it left was a mark like that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.27,0:58:29.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,这货太厉害了\N{\fs90}This thing is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.91,0:58:37.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管那俩这次打什么歪主意\N{\fs90}Whatever those two are planning this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.04,0:58:39.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,都没用\N{\fs90}it won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.64,0:58:43.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们可坏不了我的汤了\N{\fs90}They won't be able to damage my soup now.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.39,0:58:49.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,无人机反馈稳定\N{\fs90}Drone feed stabilised.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.79,0:58:51.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,开阔地带发现车辆\N{\fs90}Vehicle spotted in the open.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.56,0:58:54.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,45号舰准备截获目标\N{\fs90}45 stand by to engage target.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.49,0:58:56.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,45号舰已截获目标\N{\fs90}45 stood to engage target.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.70,0:59:08.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,这炮弹 比我们从坦克里打的那发\N{\fs90}This shell... is twice as powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.81,0:59:13.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,威力要大2倍\N{\fs90}as the shell we fired from the tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.34,0:59:16.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,它能打击20公里的目标\N{\fs90}And it can hit a target 13 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.65,0:59:23.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,装填弹药\N{\fs90}Loading weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.70,0:59:32.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,指挥室 弹药已装填 准备完毕\N{\fs90}Hot room, gun loaded. Gun ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.33,0:59:33.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,执行开火程序\N{\fs90}Fire mission,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.67,0:59:38.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,目标编号 UT 1805\N{\fs90}target number Uniform Tango 1805.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.57,0:59:40.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,海拔35\N{\fs90}Altitude 35.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.71,0:59:43.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,距离 4600\N{\fs90}Direction 4600.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.81,0:59:48.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,炮目线 方位130 高低角68\N{\fs90}Gun target line 130. Ready 68.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.71,0:59:50.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,同意发射\N{\fs90}Command approve.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.45,0:59:52.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,45号舰 准备干预\N{\fs90}45. Engage.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.35,0:59:55.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,批准发射 45号舰 发射\N{\fs90}Command approve. 45. Fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.79,1:00:05.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们觉得无聊了 发现我无法伤害\N{\fs90}They're bored. They've realised I'm unhurtable...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.43,1:00:07.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,就放弃了\N{\fs90}...and given up.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.27,1:00:10.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,5秒命中目标\N{\fs90}Five seconds to impact.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.87,1:00:12.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们可能觉得这很有趣\N{\fs90}They probably think it's really funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.67,1:00:14.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们还以为我在外面\N{\fs90}They probably think I'm out here all...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.58,1:00:26.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,45 目标摧毁\N{\fs90}45. Target destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.23,1:00:42.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了\N{\fs90}Now,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.03,1:00:45.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,后来我们去残骸看了一圈\N{\fs90}we went through the wreckage afterwards
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.74,1:00:49.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是哈蒙德的遗骸了\N{\fs90}and this is all that remains of Richard Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.34,1:00:51.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,他化成灰了 但我们知道就是他\N{\fs90}He's just dust, and we know it is Hammond
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.28,1:00:54.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我们找到了颗\N{\fs90}because we found this suspiciously white tooth...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.75,1:00:57.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,白得出奇的牙齿\N{\fs90}...in it. That's...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.82,1:01:01.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,-就是他 -没错了\N{\fs90}- That's him. - That's him.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.92,1:01:05.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 末日族们 你们看\N{\fs90}So, there you are, preppers.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.26,1:01:08.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德悲壮的遗骸告诉我们\N{\fs90}The tragic remains of Richard Hammond are proof positive
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.69,1:01:11.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们的爱好是完全没意义的\N{\fs90}that your hobby is utterly pointless.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.76,1:01:14.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你把他撒了 -把他洒向地板\N{\fs90}- You spilled him! - Spilt him on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.90,1:01:16.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,你把他弄在鞋上了\N{\fs90}Now you've got him all over your shoes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.67,1:01:18.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,我知道 他就算化成灰都那么讨厌\N{\fs90}I know. Even when he's dust, he's annoying.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.77,1:01:20.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管了\N{\fs90}Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.40,1:01:21.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,伴随着这可怕的失望之情\N{\fs90}On that terrible disappointment,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.74,1:01:23.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,是结束的时候了\N{\fs90}it is time to end.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.78,1:01:25.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,应该把他弄走了\N{\fs90}He's pretty much gone now.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.11,1:01:26.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,感谢您的收看\N{\fs90}Thank you very much for watching.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.48,1:01:28.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,下次再见\N{\fs90}See you next time. Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.11,1:01:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,
